-- # Class: AdjustableDate Description: A class for defining a date that shall be subject to adjustment if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: unadjustedDate Description: A date subject to adjustment. While in FpML this date is required, this cardinality constraint has been relaxed as part of the CDM in order to support the FRA representation, which effective and termination dates are specified in FpML as adjusted dates.
--     * Slot: adjustedDate Description: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
--     * Slot: dateAdjustments_id Description: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.
--     * Slot: dateAdjustmentsReference_id Description: A pointer style reference to date adjustments defined elsewhere in the document.
-- # Class: AdjustableDates Description: A class for defining a series of dates that shall be subject to adjustment if they would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the dates.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: PricingDates_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: dateAdjustments_id Description: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.
-- # Class: AdjustableOrAdjustedDate Description: A class for defining a date that shall be subject to adjustment if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: unadjustedDate Description: A date subject to adjustment.
--     * Slot: adjustedDate Description: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
--     * Slot: dateAdjustments_id Description: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.
-- # Class: AdjustableOrAdjustedOrRelativeDate Description: This Rosetta class specifies the date as either an unadjusted, adjusted or relative date. It supplements the features of the AdjustableOrAdjustedDate to support the credit default swap option premium, which uses the relative date construct.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: unadjustedDate Description: A date subject to adjustment.
--     * Slot: adjustedDate Description: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
--     * Slot: dateAdjustments_id Description: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.
--     * Slot: relativeDate_id Description: A date specified as some offset to another date (the anchor date).
-- # Class: AdjustableOrRelativeDate Description: A class giving the choice between defining a date as an explicit date together with applicable adjustments or as relative to some other (anchor) date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: adjustableDate_id Description: A date that shall be subject to adjustment if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.
--     * Slot: relativeDate_id Description: A date specified as some offset to another date (the anchor date).
-- # Class: AdjustableOrRelativeDates Description: A class giving the choice between defining a series of dates as an explicit list of dates together with applicable adjustments or as relative to some other series of (anchor) dates.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: adjustableDates_id Description: A series of dates that shall be subject to adjustment if they would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.
--     * Slot: relativeDates_id Description: A series of dates specified as some offset to another series of dates (the anchor dates).
-- # Class: AdjustedRelativeDateOffset Description: A type defining a date (referred to as the derived date) as a relative offset from another date (referred to as the anchor date) plus optional date adjustments.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: businessDayConvention Description: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day, as specified by an ISDA convention (e.g. Following, Precedent).
--     * Slot: dateRelativeTo Description: Specifies the anchor as an href attribute. The href attribute value is a pointer style reference to the element or component elsewhere in the document where the anchor date is defined.
--     * Slot: adjustedDate Description: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
--     * Slot: dayType Description: In the case of an offset specified as a number of days, this element defines whether consideration is given as to whether a day is a good business day or not. If a day type of business days is specified then non-business days are ignored when calculating the offset. The financial business centers to use for determination of business days are implied by the context in which this element is used. This element must only be included when the offset is specified as a number of days. If the offset is zero days then the dayType element should not be included.
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying an offset relative to another date, e.g. -2 days.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month or year of the stream. If the periodMultiplier value is 0 (zero) then period must contain the value D (day).
--     * Slot: relativeDateAdjustments_id Description: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the relative date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.
--     * Slot: businessCenters_id Description: The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
--     * Slot: businessCentersReference_id Description: A pointer style reference to a set of financial business centers defined elsewhere in the document. This set of business centers is used to determine whether a particular day is a business day or not.
-- # Class: BusinessCenters Description: A class for specifying the business day calendar location used in determining whether a day is a business day or not, either by specifying this business center by reference to an enumerated list that is maintained by the FpML standard, or by reference to such specification when it exists elsewhere as part of the instance document. This class corresponds to the FpML BusinessCentersOrReference.model.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: businessCentersReference_id Description: A reference to a financial business center location specified elsewhere in the instance document.
-- # Class: BusinessCenterTime Description: A class for defining a time with respect to a business day calendar location. For example, 11:00:00 GBLO.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: hourMinuteTime Description: A time specified in hh:mm:ss format where the second component must be '00', e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00.
--     * Slot: businessCenter Description: A code identifying a business day calendar location. A business day calendar location is drawn from the list identified by the business day calendar location enumeration.
-- # Class: BusinessDateRange Description: A class defining a range of contiguous business days by defining an unadjusted first date, an unadjusted last date and a business day convention and business centers for adjusting the first and last dates if they would otherwise fall on a non business day in the specified business centers. The days between the first and last date must also be good business days in the specified centers to be counted in the range.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: businessDayConvention Description: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day, as specified by an ISDA convention (e.g. Following, Precedent).
--     * Slot: startDate Description: The first date of a date range.
--     * Slot: endDate Description: The last date of a date range.
--     * Slot: businessCenters_id Description: The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
-- # Class: BusinessDayAdjustments Description: A class defining the business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting any relevant date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business center.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: businessDayConvention Description: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day.
--     * Slot: businessCenters_id Description: The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
-- # Class: DateRange Description: A class defining a contiguous series of calendar dates. The date range is defined as all the dates between and including the start and the end date. The start date must fall on or before the end date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: startDate Description: The first date of a date range.
--     * Slot: endDate Description: The last date of a date range.
-- # Class: DateList Description: List of dates.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: DateTimeList Description: List of dateTimes.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: Frequency Description: A class for defining a date frequency, e.g. one day, three months, through the combination of an integer value and a standardized period value that is specified as part of an enumeration.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2, or 3. If the period value is T (Term) then period multiplier must contain the value 1.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month, year or term of the stream.
-- # Class: Offset Description: A class defining an offset used in calculating a new date relative to a reference date, e.g. calendar days, business days, commodity Business days, etc.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: dayType Description: In the case of an offset specified as a number of days, this element defines whether consideration is given as to whether a day is a good business day or not. If a day type of business days is specified then non-business days are ignored when calculating the offset. The financial business centers to use for determination of business days are implied by the context in which this element is used. This element must only be included when the offset is specified as a number of days. If the offset is zero days then the dayType element should not be included.
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying an offset relative to another date, e.g. -2 days.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month or year of the stream. If the periodMultiplier value is 0 (zero) then period must contain the value D (day).
-- # Class: CustomisableOffset Description: A class to specify an offset either as a normalized [multiplier, period, dayType] or as a custom provision of type string.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: customProvision
--     * Slot: offset_id
-- # Class: Period Description: A class to define recurring periods or time offsets.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying an offset relative to another date, e.g. -2 days.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month or year of the stream. If the periodMultiplier value is 0 (zero) then period must contain the value D (day).
-- # Class: RelativeDates Description: A class describing a set of dates defined as relative to another set of dates.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: periodSkip Description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.
--     * Slot: businessDayConvention Description: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day, as specified by an ISDA convention (e.g. Following, Precedent).
--     * Slot: dateRelativeTo Description: Specifies the anchor as an href attribute. The href attribute value is a pointer style reference to the element or component elsewhere in the document where the anchor date is defined.
--     * Slot: adjustedDate Description: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
--     * Slot: dayType Description: In the case of an offset specified as a number of days, this element defines whether consideration is given as to whether a day is a good business day or not. If a day type of business days is specified then non-business days are ignored when calculating the offset. The financial business centers to use for determination of business days are implied by the context in which this element is used. This element must only be included when the offset is specified as a number of days. If the offset is zero days then the dayType element should not be included.
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying an offset relative to another date, e.g. -2 days.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month or year of the stream. If the periodMultiplier value is 0 (zero) then period must contain the value D (day).
--     * Slot: scheduleBounds_id Description: The first and last dates of a schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of values in a reference series of dates.
--     * Slot: businessCenters_id Description: The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
--     * Slot: businessCentersReference_id Description: A pointer style reference to a set of financial business centers defined elsewhere in the document. This set of business centers is used to determine whether a particular day is a business day or not.
-- # Class: RelativeDateOffset Description: A class defining a date (referred to as the derived date) as a relative offset from another date (referred to as the anchor date). If the anchor date is itself an adjustable date then the offset is assumed to be calculated from the adjusted anchor date. A number of different scenarios can be supported, namely; 1) the derived date may simply be a number of calendar periods (days, weeks, months or years) preceding or following the anchor date; 2) the unadjusted derived date may be a number of calendar periods (days, weeks, months or years) preceding or following the anchor date with the resulting unadjusted derived date subject to adjustment in accordance with a specified business day convention, i.e. the derived date must fall on a good business day; 3) the derived date may be a number of business days preceding or following the anchor date. Note that the businessDayConvention specifies any required adjustment to the unadjusted derived date. A negative or positive value in the periodMultiplier indicates whether the unadjusted derived precedes or follows the anchor date. The businessDayConvention should contain a value NONE if the day type element contains a value of Business (since specifying a negative or positive business days offset would already guarantee that the derived date would fall on a good business day in the specified business centers).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: businessDayConvention Description: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day, as specified by an ISDA convention (e.g. Following, Precedent).
--     * Slot: dateRelativeTo Description: Specifies the anchor as an href attribute. The href attribute value is a pointer style reference to the element or component elsewhere in the document where the anchor date is defined.
--     * Slot: adjustedDate Description: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
--     * Slot: dayType Description: In the case of an offset specified as a number of days, this element defines whether consideration is given as to whether a day is a good business day or not. If a day type of business days is specified then non-business days are ignored when calculating the offset. The financial business centers to use for determination of business days are implied by the context in which this element is used. This element must only be included when the offset is specified as a number of days. If the offset is zero days then the dayType element should not be included.
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying an offset relative to another date, e.g. -2 days.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month or year of the stream. If the periodMultiplier value is 0 (zero) then period must contain the value D (day).
--     * Slot: businessCenters_id Description: The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
--     * Slot: businessCentersReference_id Description: A pointer style reference to a set of financial business centers defined elsewhere in the document. This set of business centers is used to determine whether a particular day is a business day or not.
-- # Class: TimeZone Description: The time alongside with the timezone location information. This class makes use of the FpML TimezoneLocation construct.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: time Description: The observation time.
--     * Slot: location Description: FpML specifies the timezoneLocationScheme by reference to the Time Zone Database (a.k.a. tz database) maintained by IANA, the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.
-- # Class: DirectOrRelativeTime Description: Represents a time definition that can be either an absolute (direct) time or a time calculated relative to another referenced time. Either one directTime or one relativeTime should be provided
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: directTime_id Description: An absolute time value expressed in a specific time zone.
--     * Slot: relativeTime_id Description: A time value calculated relative to another reference time.
-- # Class: RelativeTime Description: Defines a time value calculated relative to a reference time. The final value is derived by applying any offset and rounding rules inherited from RelativeTimeOffset to the reference time.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: offsetTimeUnit Description: The unit of time for the offset (e.g., seconds, minutes, hours, days).
--     * Slot: offsetMultiplier Description: A time offset multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying a negative offset, e.g. -2 hours.
--     * Slot: timeRelativeTo_id Description: The reference time zone or base time from which the relative time is calculated.
--     * Slot: rounding_id Description: Optional rules that define how the calculated time should be rounded after the offset has been applied.
-- # Class: RelativeTimeOffset Description: Describes how a time is offset from a reference point, including the unit, magnitude, and rounding behavior.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: offsetTimeUnit Description: The unit of time for the offset (e.g., seconds, minutes, hours, days).
--     * Slot: offsetMultiplier Description: A time offset multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying a negative offset, e.g. -2 hours.
--     * Slot: rounding_id Description: Optional rules that define how the calculated time should be rounded after the offset has been applied.
-- # Class: TimeRounding Description: Specifies how a calculated time should be rounded, including both the direction of rounding and the unit to which the time is rounded. Rounding is applied after all offsets have been calculated.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: roundingDirection Description: The direction in which rounding is performed (e.g., up, down, or to the nearest value).
--     * Slot: roundToUnit Description: The time unit to which the value should be rounded (e.g., minute, hour, day).
-- # Class: PeriodRange Description: Indicates The period range defined as either a lower and upper period bound, or both.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: lowerBound_id Description: Specifies the lower bound of a period range, e.g. greater than or equal to 5Y.
--     * Slot: upperBound_id Description: Specifies the upper bound of a period range, e.g. less than to 10Y.
-- # Class: PeriodBound Description: Indicator to specify if the period bound is defined as a period and whether the bound is inclusive.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: inclusive Description: Specifies whether the period bound is inclusive, e.g. for a lower bound, false would indicate greater than, whereas true would indicate greater than or equal to.
--     * Slot: period_id Description: Specifies the period is to be used as the bound, e.g. 5Y.
-- # Class: AveragingSchedule Description: Class to representing a method for generating a series of dates.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: startDate Description: Date on which this period begins.
--     * Slot: endDate Description: Date on which this period ends.
--     * Slot: TriggerEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: AveragingPeriod_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: averagingPeriodFrequency_id Description: The frequency at which averaging period occurs with the regular part of the valuation schedule and their roll date convention.
-- # Class: AdjustableRelativeOrPeriodicDates Description: A class giving the choice between defining a series of dates as an explicit list of dates together with applicable adjustments or as relative to some other series of (anchor) dates, or as a calculation period schedule.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: PaymentDateSchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: adjustableDates_id Description: A series of dates that shall be subject to adjustment if they would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.
--     * Slot: relativeDates_id Description: A series of dates specified as some offset to another series of dates (the anchor dates).
--     * Slot: periodicDates_id Description: A calculation period schedule.
-- # Class: PeriodicDates Description: A class for specifying a calculation period schedule.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: dayType Description: Denotes the enumerated values to specify the day type classification used in counting the number of days between two dates.
--     * Slot: startDate_id Description: The start date of the calculation period. FpML specifies that for interest rate swaps this date must only be specified if it is not equal to the effective date. It is always specified in the case of equity swaps and credit default swaps with periodic payments. This date may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.
--     * Slot: endDate_id Description: The end date of the calculation period. FpML specifies that for interest rate swaps this date must only be specified if it is not equal to the termination date. It is always specified in the case of equity swaps with periodic payments. This date may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.
--     * Slot: periodFrequency_id Description: The frequency at which calculation period end dates occur with the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.
--     * Slot: periodDatesAdjustments_id Description: The specification of the business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting any calculation period date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business center.
-- # Class: CalculationPeriodFrequency Description: A class to specify the frequency at which calculation period end dates occur within the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: rollConvention Description: The roll convention specifies the period term as part of a periodic schedule, i.e. the calculation period end date within the regular part of the calculation period. The value could be a rule, e.g. IMM Settlement Dates, which is the 3rd Wednesday of the month, or it could be a specific day of the month, such as the first day of the applicable month. It is used in conjunction with a frequency and the regular period start date of a calculation period.
--     * Slot: balanceOfFirstPeriod Description: Indicates, when true, that that the first Calculation Period should run from the Effective Date to the end of the calendar period in which the Effective Date falls, e.g. Jan 15 - Jan 31 if the calculation periods are one month long and Effective Date is Jan 15. If false, the first Calculation Period should run from the Effective Date for one whole period, e.g. Jan 15 to Feb 14 if the calculation periods are one month long and Effective Date is Jan 15. Mostly used in Commmodity Swaps.
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2, or 3. If the period value is T (Term) then period multiplier must contain the value 1.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month, year or term of the stream.
-- # Class: CalculationFrequency Description: Represents the parameters for describing how often something (such as collateral interest) is to be calculated.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: monthOfYear Description: Specifies the month of the year if used.
--     * Slot: dayOfMonth Description: Specifies the day of the month if used.
--     * Slot: dayOfWeek Description: Specifies the day of the week if used.
--     * Slot: weekOfMonth Description: Specifies the week of the month if used.
--     * Slot: offsetDays Description: Specifies how many days from the trigger event should the payment occur.
--     * Slot: period_id Description: Specifies the time period at which calculation is performed, e.g. 1 month.
--     * Slot: dateLocation_id Description: Specifies where is the time measured.
-- # Class: UnitType Description: Defines the unit to be used for price, quantity, or other purposes
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: capacityUnit Description: Provides an enumerated value for a capacity unit, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
--     * Slot: weatherUnit Description: Provides an enumerated values for a weather unit, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
--     * Slot: financialUnit Description: Provides an enumerated value for financial units, generally used in the context of defining quantities for securities.
--     * Slot: currency Description: Defines the currency to be used as a unit for a price, quantity, or other purpose.
-- # Class: MeasureBase Description: Provides an abstract type to define a measure as a number associated to a unit. This type is abstract because all its attributes are optional. The types that extend it can specify further existence constraints.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: Measure Description: Defines a concrete measure as a number associated to a unit. It extends MeasureBase by requiring the value attribute to be present. A measure may be unit-less so the unit attribute is still optional.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: MeasureSchedule Description: A set of measures, all in the same unit, where the values are defined through a schedule of steps. The initial value may be defined either as part of the steps, or using the single amount attribute.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: QuantitySchedule Description: Specifies a quantity schedule to be associated to a financial product to represent a trade amount. This data type extends MeasureSchedule with several unit or multiplier attributes that are used to define financial quantities. This data type is generically based on a schedule and can also be used to represent a quantity as a single value.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: multiplier_id Description: Defines an optional number that the quantity should be multiplied by to derive a total quantity. This number is associated to a unit. For example in the case of the Coal (API2) CIF ARA (ARGUS-McCloskey) Futures Contract on the CME, where the unit would be contracts, the multiplier value would 1,000 and the mulitiplier unit would be 1,000 MT (Metric Tons).
--     * Slot: frequency_id Description: Defines the frequency to be used when defining a quantity. For example a quantity may be specified as a number of barrels of oil per day, which needs multiplying by the number of days in the relevant period to get the total quantity as a number of barrels.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: Quantity Description: Specifies a quantity as a single value to be associated to a financial product, for example a transfer amount resulting from a trade. This data type extends QuantitySchedule and requires that only the single amount value exists.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: multiplier_id Description: Defines an optional number that the quantity should be multiplied by to derive a total quantity. This number is associated to a unit. For example in the case of the Coal (API2) CIF ARA (ARGUS-McCloskey) Futures Contract on the CME, where the unit would be contracts, the multiplier value would 1,000 and the mulitiplier unit would be 1,000 MT (Metric Tons).
--     * Slot: frequency_id Description: Defines the frequency to be used when defining a quantity. For example a quantity may be specified as a number of barrels of oil per day, which needs multiplying by the number of days in the relevant period to get the total quantity as a number of barrels.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: NonNegativeQuantity Description: Specifies a quantity as a non-negative number, which condition is enforced through a data rule that only applies to the extending class.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: multiplier_id Description: Defines an optional number that the quantity should be multiplied by to derive a total quantity. This number is associated to a unit. For example in the case of the Coal (API2) CIF ARA (ARGUS-McCloskey) Futures Contract on the CME, where the unit would be contracts, the multiplier value would 1,000 and the mulitiplier unit would be 1,000 MT (Metric Tons).
--     * Slot: frequency_id Description: Defines the frequency to be used when defining a quantity. For example a quantity may be specified as a number of barrels of oil per day, which needs multiplying by the number of days in the relevant period to get the total quantity as a number of barrels.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: NonNegativeStep Description: A class defining a step date and non-negative step value pair. This step definitions are used to define varying rate or amount schedules, e.g. a notional amortisation or a step-up coupon schedule.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: stepDate Description: The date on which the associated stepValue becomes effective. This day may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.
--     * Slot: stepValue Description: The non-negative rate or amount which becomes effective on the associated stepDate. A rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.
-- # Class: NonNegativeQuantitySchedule
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
--     * Slot: multiplier_id Description: Defines an optional number that the quantity should be multiplied by to derive a total quantity. This number is associated to a unit. For example in the case of the Coal (API2) CIF ARA (ARGUS-McCloskey) Futures Contract on the CME, where the unit would be contracts, the multiplier value would 1,000 and the mulitiplier unit would be 1,000 MT (Metric Tons).
--     * Slot: frequency_id Description: Defines the frequency to be used when defining a quantity. For example a quantity may be specified as a number of barrels of oil per day, which needs multiplying by the number of days in the relevant period to get the total quantity as a number of barrels.
--     * Slot: unit_id Description: Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
-- # Class: Rounding Description: Defines rounding rules and precision to be used in the rounding of a number.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: roundingDirection Description: Specifies the rounding rounding rule as up, down, or nearest.
--     * Slot: precision Description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places when the number is evaluated in decimal form (not percentage), e.g. 0.09876543 rounded to the nearest 5 decimal places is  0.0987654.
-- # Class: Schedule Description: A class defining a schedule of rates or amounts in terms of an initial value and then a series of step date and value pairs. On each step date the rate or amount changes to the new step value. The series of step date and value pairs are optional. If not specified, this implies that the initial value remains unchanged over time.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: The initial rate or amount, as the case may be. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.
-- # Class: DatedValue Description: Defines a date and value pair. This definition is used for varying rate or amount schedules, e.g. a notional amortisation or a step-up coupon schedule.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: date Description: The date on which the associated step value becomes effective. This day may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.
--     * Slot: value Description: The rate of amount which becomes effective on the associated step date. A rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.
--     * Slot: MeasureSchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: QuantitySchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Quantity_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: NonNegativeQuantity_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: NonNegativeQuantitySchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Schedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: PriceSchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Price_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Money_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: AmountSchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: NumberRange Description: The number range defined as either a lower and upper number bound, or both.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: lowerBound_id Description: The lower bound of a number range, e.g. greater than or equal to 5.
--     * Slot: upperBound_id Description: The upper bound of a number range, e.g. less than 10.
-- # Class: NumberBound Description: The number bound is defined as a number and whether the bound is inclusive.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: number Description: The number to be used as the bound, e.g. 5.
--     * Slot: inclusive Description: Whether the number bound is inclusive, e.g. for a lower bound, false would indicate greater than, whereas true would indicate greater than or equal to.
-- # Class: MoneyRange Description: The money range defined as either a lower and upper money bound, or both.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: lowerBound_id Description: The lower bound of a money range, e.g. greater than or equal to 1,000 USD.
--     * Slot: upperBound_id Description: The upper bound of a money range, e.g. less than 10,000 USD.
-- # Class: MoneyBound Description: The money bound is defined as a money amount and whether the bound is inclusive.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: inclusive Description: Whether the money amount bound is inclusive, e.g. for a lower bound, false would indicate greater than, whereas true would indicate greater than or equal to.
--     * Slot: money_id Description: The money amount to be used as the bound, e.g. 1,000 USD.
-- # Class: AveragingCalculationMethod Description: Defines the ways in which multiple values can be aggregated into a single value.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isWeighted Description: Identifies whether the average values will be weighted or unweighted.
--     * Slot: calculationMethod Description: Identifies which of the Pythagorean means is being used to compute an average value.
-- # Class: AssetBase Description: The base data type to specify common attributes for all Assets.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: AssetIdentifier Description: The unique identifier for an Asset, specified using an Asset Identifier Type enumerator.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: The identifier value.
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: Defines the symbology source of the Asset Identifier, eg CUSIP, ISIN, etc.
-- # Class: InstrumentBase Description: Defines the common attributes for all Instrument data types.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: ProductIdentifier Description: Comprises an identifier and a source. The associated metadata key denotes the ability to associate a hash value to the ProductIdentifier instantiations for the purpose of model cross-referencing, in support of functionality such as the event effect and the lineage.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: Provides an identifier associated with a specific product.  The identifier is unique within the public source specified in the source attribute.
--     * Slot: source Description: Defines the source of the identifier.
--     * Slot: NonTransferableProduct_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: TaxonomyValue Description: Defines a taxonomy value as either a simple string or a more granular expression with class names and values for each class.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: Specifies the taxonomy value as a simple string, which may be associated to an external scheme.
-- # Class: Taxonomy Description: Defines the taxonomy of an object by combining a taxonomy source (i.e. the rules to classify the object) and a value (i.e. the output of those rules on the object).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: source Description: The source of the taxonomy that defines the rules for classifying the object. The taxonomy source is taken from a enumerated list of taxonomy names. Optional as the taxonomy source may not be provided.
--     * Slot: AssetBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: InstrumentBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Cash_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Commodity_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: DigitalAsset_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: ListedDerivative_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Loan_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Security_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: IndexBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: FloatingRateIndex_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: ForeignExchangeRateIndex_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: InflationIndex_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: CreditIndex_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: EquityIndex_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: OtherIndex_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Basket_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: value_id Description: The value according to that taxonomy. Optional as it may not be possible to classify the object in that taxonomy.
-- # Class: ProductTaxonomy Description: Specifies the product taxonomy, which is composed of a taxonomy value and a taxonomy source.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: primaryAssetClass Description: Classifies the most important risk class of the trade.
--     * Slot: productQualifier Description: Derived from the product payout features using a CDM product qualification function that determines the product type based on the product payout features.
--     * Slot: source Description: The source of the taxonomy that defines the rules for classifying the object. The taxonomy source is taken from a enumerated list of taxonomy names. Optional as the taxonomy source may not be provided.
--     * Slot: NonTransferableProduct_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: value_id Description: The value according to that taxonomy. Optional as it may not be possible to classify the object in that taxonomy.
-- # Class: Cash Description: An Asset that consists solely of a monetary holding in a currency. The currency of the Cash asset is held in the string Identifier (from AssetBase) and the AssetIdTypeEnum must be set to define that a CurrencyCode is set.  The function SetCashCurrency can be used to create (or update) a Cash object and the function GetCashCurrency can be used to retrieve the currency of a Cash object.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: Commodity Description: Identifies a specific commodity by referencing a product identifier or by a product definition.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: priceQuoteType Description: Describes the required quote type of the underlying price that will be observed. Example values include 'Bid, 'Ask', 'Settlement' (for a futures contract) and 'WeightedAverage' (for some published prices and indices).
--     * Slot: description Description: Provides additional information about the commodity underlier.
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: commodityProductDefinition_id Description: Specifies the commodity underlier in the event that no ISDA Commodity Reference Benchmark exists.
--     * Slot: deliveryDateReference_id Description: Specifies the parameters for identifying the relevant contract date when the commodity reference price is a futures contract.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: CommodityProductDefinition Description: Specifies the commodity underlier in the event that no ISDA Commodity Reference Price exists.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: commodityInfoPublisher Description: Specifies the publication where the commodity prices can be found.
--     * Slot: exchangeId Description:  Identifies the exchange from which the reference price should be sourced, using the scheme at the following url: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/external/exchange-id-MIC-1-0
--     * Slot: referenceFramework_id Description: Specifies the type of commodity.
--     * Slot: priceSource_id Description: Specifies a publication that provides the commodity price, including, where applicable the details of where in the publication the price is published.  Applicable when the commodity reference price is not a futures contract
-- # Class: DeliveryDateParameters Description: Specifies a specific date or the parameters for identifying the relevant contract date when the commodity reference price is a futures contract.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CommodityReferenceFramework Description: Specifies the type of commodity.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: commodityName Description: Identifies the commodity more specifically. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions SubAnnex A, including the subCommodity and additional qualifiers, but should be limited to 256 characters or less.
--     * Slot: capacityUnit Description: Provides an enumerated value for a capacity unit, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
--     * Slot: weatherUnit Description: Provides an enumerated values for a weather unit, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
--     * Slot: currency Description: Defines the currency in which the commodity is priced.
-- # Class: DigitalAsset Description: An Asset that exists only in digital form, eg Bitcoin or Ethereum, that is not backed by other Assets; excludes the digital representation of other Assets, eg coins or Tokenised assets.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: ListedDerivative Description: A securitized derivative on another asset.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: deliveryTerm Description: Also called contract month or delivery month. However, it's not always a month. It is usually expressed using a code, e.g. Z23 would be the Dec 2023 contract, (Z = December). For crude oil, the corresponding contract might be called CLZ23. Optional as this can be uniquely identified in the identifier.
--     * Slot: optionType Description: The type of option, ie Put or Call. Left empty if it is a Future.
--     * Slot: strike Description: Specifies the strike of the option.
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: Loan Description: Identifies a loan by referencing an asset identifier and through an optional set of attributes.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: lien Description: Specifies the seniority level of the lien.
--     * Slot: facilityType Description: Specifies the type of loan facility (letter of credit, revolving, ...).
--     * Slot: creditAgreementDate Description: Specifies the credit agreement date is the closing date (the date where the agreement has been signed) for the loans in the credit agreement. Funding of the facilities occurs on (or sometimes a little after) the Credit Agreement date. This underlier attribute is used to help identify which of the company's outstanding loans are being referenced by knowing to which credit agreement it belongs. ISDA Standards Terms Supplement term: Date of Original Credit Agreement.
--     * Slot: tranche Description: Denotes the loan tranche that is subject to the derivative transaction. It will typically be referenced as the Bloomberg tranche number. ISDA Standards Terms Supplement term: Bloomberg Tranche Number.
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: CollateralTaxonomy Description: Specifies the collateral taxonomy, which is composed of a taxonomy value and a taxonomy source.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: taxonomySource Description: Specifies the taxonomy source.
--     * Slot: taxonomyValue_id Description: Specifies the taxonomy value.
-- # Class: CollateralTaxonomyValue Description: Specifies the collateral taxonomy value, either as a specified enumeration or as a string.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: Security Description: Identifies a security by referencing an identifier and by specifying the sector.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: securityType Description: Identifies the type of security using an enumerated list.
--     * Slot: fundType Description: Identifies the type of fund.
--     * Slot: isExchangeListed Description: Defines whether the Asset is listed on a public exchange.
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Specifies the type of asset.
--     * Slot: debtType_id Description: Identifies the type of debt and selected debt economics.
--     * Slot: equityType_id Description: Identifies the type of equity.
--     * Slot: exchange_id Description: If the Asset is listed, defines the public exchange of the listing.
-- # Class: EquityType
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: equityType Description: Identifies the type of equity.
--     * Slot: depositaryReceipt
-- # Class: DebtType Description: Specifies the type of debt security.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: DebtEconomics Description: Specifies selected economics of a debt security.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: seniority Description: Specifies the order of repayment in the event of a sale or bankruptcy of the issuer or a related party (eg guarantor).
--     * Slot: interest Description: Specifies the general rule for periodic interest rate payment.
--     * Slot: principal Description: Specifies the general rule for repayment of principal.
--     * Slot: DebtType_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: secured_id Description: Specifies the type of secured debt.
--     * Slot: redemption_id Description: Specifies the general rule for redemption of a debt security.
-- # Class: DebtRedemption Description: Specifies the redemption features and whether the redemption right is exercised at the discretion of the issuer or the holder.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: redemptionType Description: Specifies the contractual redemption or conversion features associated with a debt security.
--     * Slot: putCall Description: Specifies the embedded option feature of a debt security.
--     * Slot: party Description: Specifies whether the debt security is redeemed at the election of the Issuer/Holder.
-- # Class: SecuredDebt
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: securedType Description: Specifies the type of secured debt product.
--     * Slot: assetBacked Description: Specifies the type of Asset Backed Security.
--     * Slot: collateralizedObligation Description: Specifies the type of Collateralized Obligation.
--     * Slot: coveredBond Description: Specifies the type of Covered Bond.
--     * Slot: propertyType Description: Specifies the type of property when the security is linked to a property asset.
-- # Class: CollateralGuarantorType Description: Specifies the origin of entity guaranteeing the collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: guarantorType Description: Specifies the origin of entity guaranteeing the collateral.
-- # Class: CollateralIssuerType Description: Represents a class to allow specification of the type of entity issuing the collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: issuerType Description: Specifies the origin of entity issuing the collateral.
--     * Slot: supraNationalType Description: Specifies debt issued by international organisations and multilateral banks.
--     * Slot: quasiGovernmentType_id Description: Specifies debt issues by institutions or bodies, typically constituted by statute, with a function mandated by the government and subject to government supervision inclusive of profit- and non-profit making bodies. Includes the US Agencies and GSEs and the EU concept of public sector entities. Excluding any entities which are also Regional Government.
--     * Slot: regionalGovernmentType_id Description: Specifies Regional government, local authority or municipal.
--     * Slot: specialPurposeVehicleType_id Description: Specifies a subsidiary company that is formed to undertake a specific business purpose of acquisition and financing of specific assets on a potentially limited recourse basis dependent of how it is designed. E.g. asset backed securities, including securitisations.
-- # Class: QuasiGovernmentIssuerType Description: Represents a class to allow specification of different types of Quasi Government collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: sovereignEntity Description: True if sovereign entity (e.g. not separate legal personality from sovereign) or false if non-sovereign entity (e.g. separate legal personality from sovereign).
--     * Slot: sovereignRecourse Description: Applies to non-sovereign entity (e.g. separate legal personality from sovereign).  True if entity has recourse to sovereign (e.g. debt guaranteed by government).  False if entity does not have recourse to sovereign.
-- # Class: RegionalGovernmentIssuerType Description: Represents a class to allow specification of different type of Regional government collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: sovereignRecourse Description: Applies to regional governments, local authorities or municipals.  True if entity has recourse to sovereign (e.g. debt guaranteed by government).  False if entity does not have recourse to sovereign.
-- # Class: SpecialPurposeVehicleIssuerType Description: Represents a class to allow specification of different types of special purpose vehicle (SPV) collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: creditRisk Description: Indicates tranched or untranched credit risk.
-- # Class: TaxonomyClassification
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: className Description: The name defined by the classification system for a specific attribute in the taxonomy
--     * Slot: value Description: The value set by the taxonomy that is specific to the className attribute.
--     * Slot: description Description: A description of the class.
--     * Slot: ordinal Description: In the case of multi-layered hierarchical classification systems such as commodity classification, the layer the value and className occupy in the classification hierarchy, where 1 represents the top-layer.
--     * Slot: TaxonomyValue_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: AssetType Description: Represents a class to allow specification of the asset product type.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: assetType Description: Represents a filter based on the type of collateral asset.
--     * Slot: securityType Description: Represents a filter based on the type of security.
--     * Slot: fundType Description: Represents a filter based on the type of fund.
--     * Slot: debtType_id Description: Represents a filter based on the type of bond.
--     * Slot: equityType_id Description: Represents a filter based on the type of equity.
-- # Class: PriceSource Description: Specifies a publication that provides the commodity price, including, where applicable, the details of where in the publication the price is published.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: pricePublisher Description: Defines a publication in which the price can be found. (e.g Gas Daily, Platts Bloomberg. Commodity publishers can be found at this URL:  http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-information-provider>
--     * Slot: priceSourceLocation Description: Specifies the location of the price which may be a specific page, electornic screen name, or a code (e.g. a RIC code) where the price can be found.
--     * Slot: priceSourceHeading Description: Specifies the heading or field name for the price  on a given page or screen, where applicable.
--     * Slot: priceSourceTime Description: Specifies the time at which the price should be observed.
-- # Abstract Class: Asset Description: An Asset is defined as something that can be owned and transferred in the financial markets. As a choice data type, one and only one of the attributes must be used.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Abstract Class: Instrument Description: A type of Asset that is issued by one party to one or more others.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: NotDomesticCurrency Description: A class to specify the ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Currency.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: applicable Description: Indicates whether the Not Domestic Currency provision is applicable.
--     * Slot: currency Description: An explicit specification of the domestic currency. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
-- # Class: Obligations Description: A class to specify the underlying obligations of the reference entity on which protection is purchased or sold through the Credit Default Swap.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: category Description: Used in both obligations and deliverable obligations to represent a class or type of securities which apply. ISDA 2003 Term: Obligation Category/Deliverable Obligation Category.
--     * Slot: notSubordinated Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. An obligation that ranks at least equal with the most senior Reference Obligation in priority of payment or, if no Reference Obligation is specified in the related Confirmation, the obligations of the Reference Entity that are senior. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Subordinated.
--     * Slot: notSovereignLender Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation that is not primarily (majority) owed to a Sovereign or Supranational Organisation. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Sovereign Lender.
--     * Slot: notDomesticLaw Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. If the reference entity is a Sovereign, this means any obligation that is not subject to the laws of the reference entity. If the reference entity is not a sovereign, this means any obligation that is not subject to the laws of the jurisdiction of the reference entity. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Law.
--     * Slot: listed Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Indicates whether or not the obligation is quoted, listed or ordinarily purchased and sold on an exchange. ISDA 2003 Term: Listed.
--     * Slot: notDomesticIssuance Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation other than an obligation that was intended to be offered for sale primarily in the domestic market of the relevant Reference Entity. This specifies that the obligation must be an internationally recognised bond. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Issuance.
--     * Slot: fullFaithAndCreditObLiability Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published additional provisions for U.S. Municipal as Reference Entity. ISDA 2003 Term: Full Faith and Credit Obligation Liability.
--     * Slot: generalFundObligationLiability Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published additional provisions for U.S. Municipal as Reference Entity. ISDA 2003 Term: General Fund Obligation Liability.
--     * Slot: revenueObligationLiability Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published additional provisions for U.S. Municipal as Reference Entity. ISDA 2003 Term: Revenue Obligation Liability.
--     * Slot: notContingent Description: OTE: Only allowed as an obligation characteristic under ISDA Credit 1999. In essence Not Contingent means the repayment of principal cannot be dependent on a formula/index, i.e. to prevent the risk of being delivered an instrument that may never pay any element of principal, and to ensure that the obligation is interest bearing (on a regular schedule). ISDA 2003 Term: Not Contingent.
--     * Slot: excluded Description: A free format string to specify any excluded obligations or deliverable obligations, as the case may be, of the reference entity or excluded types of obligations or deliverable obligations. ISDA 2003 Term: Excluded Obligations/Excluded Deliverable Obligations.
--     * Slot: othReferenceEntityObligations Description: This element is used to specify any other obligations of a reference entity in both obligations and deliverable obligations. The obligations can be specified free-form. ISDA 2003 Term: Other Obligations of a Reference Entity.
--     * Slot: designatedPriority Description: Applies to Loan CDS, to indicate what lien level is appropriate for a deliverable obligation. Applies to European Loan CDS, to indicate the Ranking of the obligation. Example: a 2nd lien Loan CDS would imply that the deliverable obligations are 1st or 2nd lien loans.
--     * Slot: cashSettlementOnly Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published Standard Terms Supplement for use with CDS Transactions on Leveraged Loans. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Only.
--     * Slot: deliveryOfCommitments Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published Standard Terms Supplement for use with CDS Transactions on Leveraged Loans. ISDA 2003 Term: Delivery of Commitments.
--     * Slot: continuity Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published Standard Terms Supplement for use with CDS Transactions on Leveraged Loans. ISDA 2003 Term: Continuity.
--     * Slot: specifiedCurrency_id Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. The currency or currencies in which an obligation or deliverable obligation must be payable. ISDA 2003 Term: Specified Currency.
--     * Slot: notDomesticCurrency_id Description: An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation that is payable in any currency other than the domestic currency. Domestic currency is either the currency so specified or, if no currency is specified, the currency of (a) the reference entity, if the reference entity is a sovereign, or (b) the jurisdiction in which the relevant reference entity is organised, if the reference entity is not a sovereign. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Currency.
-- # Class: SpecifiedCurrency
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: applicable Description: Indicates whether the specified currency provision is applicable.
--     * Slot: currency Description: The currency in which the specified currency is denominated. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
-- # Class: CodeList Description: A type hold a list of codes for business data validation
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identification_id Description: Identification information about the code list
-- # Class: CodeListIdentification Description: A type to identify the version of a codelist
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: description Description: A description  of the code list, e.g. A list of codes identifying business centers
--     * Slot: publicationDate Description: The most recent date the code list was published, e.g. 2021-10-05
--     * Slot: shortName Description: A short name (without whitespace) for the code list, e.g. businessCenterScheme
--     * Slot: version Description: The the most recent version of the codelist, eg. 9-1
--     * Slot: codeShortId Description: The name of the code list, e.g. business-center
--     * Slot: canonicalUri Description: Canonical URI which uniquely identifies all versions (collectively) of the referenced code list. Must be an absolute URI. Must not be used as a de facto location URI.
--     * Slot: canonicalVersionUri Description: Canonical URI which uniquely identifies a specific version of the referenced code list. Must be an absolute URI. Must not be used as a de facto location URI.
--     * Slot: locationUri Description: Suggested retrieval location for this version, in genericode format. An application must signal an error to the user if a document retrieved using a LocationUri is not in genericode format.
-- # Class: CodeValue Description: A type to hold the value of the code in a codelist
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: The value of the code, e.g. USNY
--     * Slot: description Description: A description of the meaning of the code, e.g. New York City, USA
--     * Slot: source Description: Where the code was defined,e.g. ISDA, FpML, Bloomberg
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: When the code became/becomes effective
--     * Slot: deprecatedDate Description: When the code ceased to be valid for new uses
--     * Slot: CodeList_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: AssignedIdentifier Description: A class to specify the identifier value and its associated version.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: The identifier value.
--     * Slot: version Description: The identifier version, which is specified as an integer and is meant to be incremented each time the transaction terms (whether contract or event) change. This version is made option to support the use case where the identifier is referenced without the version. The constraint that a contract and a lifecycle event need to have an associated version is enforced through data rules.
--     * Slot: Identifier_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LocationIdentifier_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: TradeIdentifier_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: PositionIdentifier_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: Identifier Description: A class to specify a generic identifier, applicable to CDM artefacts such as executions, contracts, lifecycle events and legal documents. An issuer can be associated with the actual identifier value as a way to properly qualify it.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: issuer Description: The identifier issuer, when specified explicitly alongside the identifier value (instead of being specified by reference to a party).
--     * Slot: IdentifiedList_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: UnscheduledTransfer_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: ScheduledTransfer_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: TransferBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: WorkflowStep_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreementBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: PartyAgreementIdentifier_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: EligibleCollateralSpecification_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: issuerReference_id Description: The identifier issuer, when specified by reference to a party specified as part of the transaction.
-- # Class: IdentifiedList Description: Attaches an identifier to a collection of objects, when those objects themselves can each be represented by an identifier. One use case is the representation of package transactions, where each component is a separate trade with its own identifier, and those trades are linked together as a package with its own identifier. The data type has been named generically rather than referring to 'packages' as it may have a number of other uses.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: listId_id Description: The identifier for the list. In the case of a package transaction, this would be the package identifier. This attribute is mandatory to allow the list itself to be identified.
--     * Slot: price_id Description: The price of the package.
-- # Class: LocationIdentifier Description: Specifies a location identifier. An issuer and an identifier type can be associated with the actual identifier value as a way to properly qualify it.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: locationIdentifierType Description: Specifies the nature of a location identifier.
--     * Slot: issuer Description: The identifier issuer, when specified explicitly alongside the identifier value (instead of being specified by reference to a party).
--     * Slot: issuerReference_id Description: The identifier issuer, when specified by reference to a party specified as part of the transaction.
-- # Class: Counterparty Description: Defines a counterparty enumerated value, e.g. Party1 or Party2, with an associated party reference. The product is agnostic to the actual parties to the transaction, with the party references abstracted away from the product definition and replaced by the CounterpartyEnum (e.g. values Party1 or Party2). The CounterpartyEnum can then be positioned in the product (e.g. to specify which counterparty is the payer, receiver etc) and this Counterparty type, which is positioned outside of the product definition, allows the CounterpartyEnum to be associated with an actual party reference.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: role Description: Specifies the CounterpartyEnum, e.g. either Party1 or Party2, that is associated to the partyReference.
--     * Slot: partyReference_id Description: Specifies the party that is associated to the counterparty.
-- # Class: AncillaryParty Description: Defines an ancillary role enumerated value with an associated party reference. The product is agnostic to the actual parties involved in the transaction, with the party references abstracted away from the product definition and replaced by the AncillaryRoleEnum. The AncillaryRoleEnum can then be positioned in the product and this AncillaryParty type, which is positioned outside of the product definition, allows the AncillaryRoleEnum to be associated with an actual party reference.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: role Description: Specifies the AncillaryRoleEnum that is associated to the party reference. An ancillary party is any involved party that is not one of the two principal parties to the transaction.
--     * Slot: onBehalfOf Description: Optionally specifies the counterparty that the ancillary party is acting on behalf of.
-- # Class: BuyerSeller Description: This class corresponds to the FpML BuyerSeller.model construct.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: buyer Description: Buyer party that can be resolved as one of the two principal parties to the transaction. The party that buys this instrument, i.e. pays for this instrument and receives the rights defined by it. ISDA 2002 Equity Definitions section 1.18: `Buyer` means the party specified as such in the related Confirmation. | ISDA 2006 Definitions article 12.1 (b)(i) relating to a Swaption: 'Buyer' means the party that will, on each Premium Payment Date, pay to Seller the Premium | ISDA 2006 Definitions article 12.1 (b)(ii) relating to Swap Transactions with applicable Early Termination: the party specified as such in the related Confirmation, or the Exercising Party if neither party is specified | ISDA 2006 Definitions article 12.1 (b)(iii) relating to any other Option Transaction: the party specified as such in the related Confirmation. | ISDA 2014 Credit Definition article 1.4: `Buyer` means the Fixed Rate Payer.
--     * Slot: seller Description: Seller party that can be resolved as one of the two principal parties to the transaction. The party that sells ('writes') this instrument, i.e. that grants the rights defined by this instrument and in return receives a payment for it. ISDA 2002 Equity Definitions section 1.19: `Seller` means the party specified as such in the related Confirmation. | ISDA 2006 Definitions article 12.1 (a)(i) relating to a Swaption: 'Seller' means the party the party specified as such or as writer in the related Confirmation | ISDA 2006 Definitions article 12.1 (a)(ii) relating to Swap Transactions with applicable Early Termination: the party specified as such or as writer in the related Confirmation or, if neither party is specified as such, the Non-exercising Party | ISDA 2006 Definitions article 12.1 (a)(iii) relating to any other Option Transaction: the party specified as such in the related Confirmation. | ISDA 2014 Credit Definition article 1.4: `Seller` means the Floating Rate Payer.
--     * Slot: EventCurrency_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: PayerReceiver Description: Specifies the parties responsible for making and receiving payments defined by this structure.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: payer Description: Specifies the counterparty responsible for making the payments defined by this structure.  The party is one of the two principal parties to the transaction.
--     * Slot: receiver Description: Specifies the party that receives the payments corresponding to this structure.  The party is one of the two counterparties to the transaction.
-- # Class: PartyReferencePayerReceiver Description: Specifies the parties responsible for making and receiving payments defined by this structure.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: payerPartyReference_id Description: The party responsible for making the payments defined by this structure.
--     * Slot: payerAccountReference_id Description: A reference to the account responsible for making the payments defined by this structure.
--     * Slot: receiverPartyReference_id Description: The party that receives the payments corresponding to this structure.
--     * Slot: receiverAccountReference_id Description: A reference to the account that receives the payments corresponding to this structure.
-- # Class: ReferenceBank Description: A class to describe an institution (party) identified by means of a coding scheme and an optional name.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: referenceBankId Description: An institution (party) identifier, e.g. a bank identifier code (BIC). FpML specifies a referenceBankIdScheme.
--     * Slot: referenceBankName Description: The name of the institution (party). A free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for the element.
--     * Slot: ReferenceBanks_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: ReferenceBanks Description: A class defining the list of reference institutions polled for relevant rates or prices when determining the cash settlement amount for a product where cash settlement is applicable.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: RelatedParty
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: role Description: The category of the relationship. The related party performs the role specified in this field for the base party. For example, if the role is ,Guarantor, the related party acts as a guarantor for the base party.
--     * Slot: partyReference_id Description: Reference to a party.
--     * Slot: accountReference_id Description: Reference to an account.
-- # Class: Account Description: A class to specify an account as an account number alongside, optionally. an account name, an account type, an account beneficiary and a servicing party.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: accountNumber Description: The account number.
--     * Slot: accountName Description: The name by which the account is known.
--     * Slot: accountType Description: The type of account, e.g. client, house.
--     * Slot: partyReference_id Description: A reference to the party to which the account refers to.
--     * Slot: accountBeneficiary_id Description: A reference to the party beneficiary of the account.
--     * Slot: servicingParty_id Description: The reference to the legal entity that services the account, i.e. in the books of which the account is held.
-- # Class: Address Description: A class to specify a post or street address.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: city Description: The city component of the postal address.
--     * Slot: state Description: A country subdivision used in postal addresses in some countries. For example, US states, Canadian provinces, Swiss cantons, ...
--     * Slot: country Description: The ISO 3166 standard code for the country within which the postal address is located.
--     * Slot: postalCode Description: The code, required for computerized mail sorting systems, that is allocated to a physical address by a national postal authority.
--     * Slot: ContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: NoticeContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: TransferContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: BusinessUnit Description: A class to specify an organizational unit.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: A name used to describe the organizational unit
--     * Slot: Party_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: identifier_id Description: An identifier used to uniquely identify the organizational unit
--     * Slot: contactInformation_id Description: The contact information for such business unit, when different from the contact information associated with the party.
-- # Class: ContactInformation Description: A class to specify contact information associated with a party: telephone, postal/street address, email and web page.
