-- # Class: NaturalPerson Description: A class to represent the attributes that are specific to a natural person.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: honorific Description: An honorific title, such as Mr., Ms., Dr. etc.
--     * Slot: firstName Description: The natural person's first name. It is optional in FpML.
--     * Slot: surname Description: The natural person's surname.
--     * Slot: suffix Description: Name suffix, such as Jr., III, etc.
--     * Slot: dateOfBirth Description: The natural person's date of birth.
--     * Slot: Party_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: NoticeContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: contactInformation_id Description: The contact information for such person, when different from the contact information associated with the party.
-- # Class: NaturalPersonRole Description: A class to specify the role(s) that natural person(s) may have in relation to the contract.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: Party_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: personReference_id Description: A reference to the natural person to whom the role refers to.
-- # Class: Party Description: A class to specify a party, without a qualification as to whether this party is a legal entity or a natural person, although the model provides the ability to associate a person (or set of persons) to a party, which use case would imply that such party would be a legal entity (even if not formally specified as such).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The party name.
--     * Slot: ExecutionInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreementBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: account_id Description: The account that might be associated with the party. At most one account can be specified, as it is expected that this information is used in the context of a contract or legal document where only one account per party can be associated with such object.
--     * Slot: contactInformation_id Description: The postal/street address, telephone number, email address and/or web page. If the contact information is specific to the associated business unit(s) or person (s), it should be associated with those.
-- # Class: PartyIdentifier Description: Comprises an identifier and a source. The associated metadata key denotes the ability to associate a hash value to the PartyIdentifier instantiations for the purpose of model cross-referencing, in support of functionality such as the event effect and the lineage.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: Provides an identifier associated with a party. The identifier is unique within the public source specified in the source attribute.
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: Defines the source of the identifier.
--     * Slot: Party_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: EntityIdentifier Description: Comprises an identifier and a source. The associated metadata key denotes the ability to associate a hash value to the EntityIdentifier instantiations for the purpose of model cross-referencing, in support of functionality such as the event effect and the lineage.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: Provides an identifier associated with a legal entity.
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: Defines the source of the identifier.
--     * Slot: LegalEntity_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: PersonIdentifier Description: Comprises an identifier and a source. The associated metadata key denotes the ability to associate a hash value to the PersonIdentifier instantiations for the purpose of model cross-referencing, in support of functionality such as the event effect and the lineage.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: Provides an identifier associated with a person. The identifier is unique within the public source specified in the source attribute.
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: Defines the source of the identifier.
--     * Slot: country Description: The ISO 3166 standard code for the country issuing the identifier.
--     * Slot: NaturalPerson_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: PartyRole Description: A class to specify the role(s) that party(ies) may have in relation to the execution, contract or other legal agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: role Description: The party role.
--     * Slot: ExecutionInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: partyReference_id Description: A reference to the party to which the role refers to.
--     * Slot: ownershipPartyReference_id Description: A reference to the party that has ownership of this party role information. FpML specifies that For shared trade information, this attribute will reference the originator of the data (for example, an execution facility or clearing house).
-- # Class: TelephoneNumber Description: A class to specify a telephone number as a type of phone number (e.g. work, personal, ...) alongside with the actual number.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: telephoneNumberType Description: The type of telephone number, e.g. work, mobile.
--     * Slot: number Description: The actual telephone number.
--     * Slot: ContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: NoticeContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: TransferContactInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: AncillaryEntity Description: Holds an identifier for an ancillary entity, either identified directly via its ancillary role or directly as a legal entity.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: ancillaryParty Description: Identifies a party via its ancillary role on a transaction (e.g. CCP or DCO through which the trade should be cleared.)
--     * Slot: Nationalization_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: legalEntity_id
-- # Class: ContractFormationInstruction Description: Specifies instructions to create a fully formed contract, with optional legal agreements.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: Instruction Description: Instruction to a function that will be used to perform a business event
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: BusinessEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: EventInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: primitiveInstruction_id Description: Specifies the primitive instructions that will be used to call primitive event functions.
--     * Slot: before_id Description: Specifies the trade state that will be acted on by the primitive event functions.
-- # Class: PrimitiveInstruction Description: A Primitive Instruction describes the inputs required to pass into the corresponding PrimitiveEvent function.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: SplitInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: contractFormation_id Description: Specifies instructions describing an contract formation primitive event.
--     * Slot: execution_id Description: Specifies instructions describing an execution primitive event.
--     * Slot: exercise_id Description: Specifies instructions describing an exercise primitive event.
--     * Slot: partyChange_id Description: Specifies instructions describing a party change primitive event.
--     * Slot: quantityChange_id Description: Specifies instructions describing an quantity change primitive event.
--     * Slot: reset_id Description: Specifies instructions describing a reset event.
--     * Slot: split_id Description: Specifies instructions to split a trade into multiple branches.
--     * Slot: termsChange_id Description: Specifies instructions describing a terms change primitive event.
--     * Slot: transfer_id Description: Specifies instructions describing a transfer primitive event.
--     * Slot: indexTransition_id Description: Specifies inputs needed to process a Index Transition business event.
--     * Slot: stockSplit_id Description: Specifies inputs needed to process a Stock Split business event.
--     * Slot: observation_id Description: Specifies inputs needed to process an observation.
--     * Slot: valuation_id Description: Specifies inputs needed to process an update of a valuation.
-- # Class: BusinessEvent Description: A business event represents a life cycle event of a trade. The combination of the state changes results in a qualifiable life cycle event. An example of a Business Event is a PartialTermination which is a defined by a quantity change primitive event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: eventQualifier Description: The CDM event qualifier, which corresponds to the outcome of the isEvent qualification logic which qualifies the lifecycle event as a function of its features (e.g. PartialTermination, ClearingSubmission, Novation, ...).
--     * Slot: intent Description: The intent attribute is meant to be specified when the event qualification cannot be programmatically inferred from the event features. As a result it is only associated with those primitives that can give way to such ambiguity, the quantityChange being one of those. An example of such is a reduction in the trade notional, which could be interpreted as either a trade correction (unless a maximum period of time post-event is specified as part of the qualification), a partial termination or a portfolio rebalancing in the case of an equity swap. On the other hand, an event such as the exercise is not expected to have an associated intent as there should not be ambiguity.
--     * Slot: corporateActionIntent Description: The intent of a corporate action on the position.
--     * Slot: eventDate Description: Specifies the date on which the event is taking place. This date is equal to the trade date in the case of a simple execution.  However it can be different from the trade date, for example in the case of a partial termination.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The date on which the event contractually takes effect, when different from the event date.
--     * Slot: eventTime_id Description: The time and zone of the date in which the event is taking place.
--     * Slot: effectiveTime_id Description: The time and zone of the date in which the event contractually takes effect.
--     * Slot: packageInformation_id Description: Specifies the package information in case the business event represents several trades executed as a package (hence this attribute is optional). The package information is only instantiated once at the business event level to preserve referential integrity, whereas individual trades make reference to it to identify that they are part of a package.
-- # Class: CounterpartyPositionBusinessEvent Description: A business event represents a life cycle event of a position. The combination of the state changes results in a qualifiable life cycle event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: intent Description: The intent attribute is meant to be specified when the event qualification cannot be programmatically inferred from the event features. As a result it is only associated with those primitives that can give way to such ambiguity, the quantityChange being one of those.
--     * Slot: corporateActionIntent Description: The intent of a corporate action on the position.
--     * Slot: eventDate Description: Specifies the date on which the event is taking place. This date is equal to the trade date in the case of a simple execution.  However it can be different from the trade date, for example in the case of a partial termination.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The date on which the event contractually takes effect, when different from the event date.
--     * Slot: packageInformation_id Description: Specifies the package information in case the business event represents several trades executed as a package (hence this attribute is optional). The package information is only instantiated once at the business event level to preserve referential integrity, whereas individual trades make reference to it to identify that they are part of a package.
-- # Class: ObservationInstruction Description: Specifies inputs needed to process an observation.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: observationEvent_id Description: Contains all information related to an observation.
-- # Class: ValuationInstruction Description: Specifies inputs needed to process a valuation.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: replace Description: Specifies whether the previous valuation tracks in the valuation history are removed (True) or kept (False).
-- # Class: ExecutionInstruction Description: Specifies instructions for execution of a transaction, consisting of a product, price, quantity, parties, trade identifier, execution details, and settlement terms.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: tradeDate Description: Denotes the trade/execution date.
--     * Slot: product_id Description: Defines the financial product to be executed and contract formed.
--     * Slot: executionDetails_id Description: Specifies the type and venue of execution, e.g. via voice, or electronically.
--     * Slot: tradeTime_id Description: Denotes the trade time and timezone as agreed by the parties to the trade.
--     * Slot: collateral_id Description: Detail the collateral requirement anticipated with the transaction.
--     * Slot: lotIdentifier_id Description: Lot Identifier associated with the transaction.
-- # Class: ExerciseInstruction Description: Specifies the information required to communicate the choices made by the exercising party, in a financial product endowing the party with at least one option.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: exerciseQuantity_id Description: Contains instructions for exercising the option including a quantity change, and optionally a transfer.
--     * Slot: exerciseOption_id Description: Specifies the Option Payout being exercised on the trade.
--     * Slot: exerciseDate_id Description: Specifies the date on which an option contained within the financial product would be exercised. The date may be omitted if the contractual product allows for only a single date of exercise (European exercise).
--     * Slot: exerciseTime_id Description: Specifies the time at which an option contained within the financial product woulld be exercised. The time may be omitted if the contractual product allows for only a single time of exercise (European exercise).
-- # Class: ResetInstruction Description: Defines the information needed to create a Reset Business Event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: rateRecordDate Description: Specifies the 'Rate Record Day' for a Fallback rate.  Fallback rate fixing processes typically set the fixing rate in arrears, i.e., the Fallback Rate corresponding to a Rate Record Date is set at the end of the interest accural period.  When this applies, Reset->resetDate occurs at the end of the interest period, and the Reset->rateRecordDate occurs near the start of the interest period.  The Reset->rateRecordDate and Reset->observations->observationIdentifier->observationDate will differ if a Fallback rate is unavailable on the Rate Record Date, and the latest previous available rate is used as the observation.
--     * Slot: resetDate Description: Specifies the date on which the reset is occuring.
-- # Class: CalculateTransferInstruction Description: Defines the tradeState or payout on which to create a Transfer along with all necessary resets.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: date
--     * Slot: tradeState_id
--     * Slot: payout_id
--     * Slot: payerReceiver_id
--     * Slot: quantity_id Description: Specifies quantity amount returned if not the full amount from the TradeState, e.g. partial return
-- # Class: TransferInstruction Description: Defines the payout on which to create a Transfer along with all necessary resets.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: QuantityChangeInstruction Description: Instructions required to create a Quantity Change Primitive Event, which can be either an increase, a decrease or a replacement. An increase adds a new trade lot to the original trade, whereas a decrease subtracts from an existing trade lot's quantity. A replacement updates the quantity of an existing trade lot to the new value.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: direction Description: Direction of the quantity change specified as either an increase, decrease or replacement.
-- # Class: IndexTransitionInstruction Description: Defines the information needed to create a Index Transition Business Event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: Specifies the effective date of the index transition event. This is first date on which the floating rate calculation will use the new floating rate index and adjusted spread in the floating rate calculation.
--     * Slot: cashTransfer_id Description: Specifies the cash transfer that can optionally be tied to an index transition event.
-- # Class: TermsChangeInstruction Description: Specifies instructions for terms change consisting of the new transaction terms, and the renegotiation fee.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: adjustment
--     * Slot: product_id Description: product to be changed
-- # Class: SplitInstruction Description: Specifies instructions for a split, consisting of a breakdown of instructions to be applied to each branch of the split. This instruction can be used to duplicate a trade, as in a clearing scenario, or to split a trade into smaller quantities (in which case each breakdown instruction needs to include a quantity change), as in an allocation.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: PartyChangeInstruction Description: Specifies instruction to change the party on a trade. This primitive instruction is used in a number of scenarios including: clearing, allocation and novation. The instrution must include a trade identifier, because a change of party effectively results in a different trade.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: counterparty_id Description: The new counterparty who is stepping into the trade. The stepping out counterparty is inferred based on the counterparty role that is being updated.
--     * Slot: ancillaryParty_id Description: Specifies an ancillary party to be added onto the new transaction, e.g. the original executing party in an allocation.
--     * Slot: partyRole_id Description: Specifies an additional party roles to be added on to the new transaction.
-- # Class: TradeState Description: Defines the fundamental financial information that can be changed by a Primitive Event and by extension any business or life-cycle event. Each TradeState specifies where a Trade is in its life-cycle. TradeState is a root type and as such, can be created independently to any other CDM data type, but can also be used as part of the CDM Event Model.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: BusinessEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: CounterpartyPosition_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: trade_id Description: Represents the Trade that has been effected by a business or life-cycle event.
--     * Slot: state_id Description: Represents the State of the Trade through its life-cycle.
-- # Class: CounterpartyPositionState Description: Defines the fundamental financial information that can be changed by a Primitive Event and by extension any business or life-cycle event. Each PositionState specifies where a Position is in its life-cycle. PositionState is a root type and as such, can be created independently to any other CDM data type, but can also be used as part of the CDM Event Model.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: CounterpartyPositionBusinessEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: counterpartyPosition_id Description: Represents the Position that has been effected by a business or life-cycle event.
--     * Slot: state_id Description: Represents the State of the Position through its life-cycle.
-- # Class: ObservationEvent Description: Specifies the necessary information to create any observation event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: TradeState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: CounterpartyPositionState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: creditEvent_id Description: Specifies the necessary information to create a credit event.
--     * Slot: corporateAction_id Description: Specifies the necessary information to create a corporate action.
-- # Class: Reset Description: Defines the reset value or fixing value produced in cashflow calculations, during the life-cycle of a financial instrument. The reset process defined in Create_Reset function joins product definition details with observations to compute the reset value.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: resetDate Description: Specifies the date on which the reset occurred.
--     * Slot: rateRecordDate Description: Specifies the 'Rate Record Day' for a Fallback rate.  Fallback rate fixing processes typically set the fixing rate in arrears, i.e., the Fallback Rate corresponding to a Rate Record Date is set at the end of the interest accural period.  When this applies, Reset->resetDate occurs at the end of the interest period, and the Reset->rateRecordDate occurs near the start of the interest period.  The Reset->rateRecordDate and Reset->observations->observationIdentifier->observationDate will differ if a Fallback rate is unavailable on the Rate Record Date, and the latest previous available rate is used as the observation.
--     * Slot: CalculateTransferInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: TradeState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: resetValue_id Description: Specifies the reset or fixing value. The fixing value could be a cash price, interest rate, or other value.
--     * Slot: averagingMethodology_id Description: Identifies the aggregation method to use in the case where multiple observations are used to compute the reset value and the method is not defined in a payout.
-- # Class: State Description: Defines the state of a trade at a point in the Trade's life cycle. Trades have many state dimensions, all of which are represented here. For example, states useful for position keeping are represented alongside those needed for regulatory reporting.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: positionState Description: Identifies the state of the position, to distinguish if just executed, formed, already settled, closed, etc.
--     * Slot: closedState_id Description: Represents the qualification of what led to the trade's closure alongside the dates on which this closure took effect.
-- # Class: TransferState Description: Defines the fundamental financial information associated with a Transfer event. Each TransferState specifies where a Transfer is in its life-cycle. TransferState is a root type and as such, can be created independently to any other CDM data type, but can also be used as part of the CDM Event Model.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: transferStatus Description: Represents the State of the Transfer through its life-cycle.
--     * Slot: TransferInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: TradeState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: transfer_id Description: Represents the Transfer that has been effected by a business or life-cycle event.
-- # Class: UnscheduledTransfer Description: An ad-hoc transfer instigated by a party to the contract.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: transferType Description: Specifies the type of unscheduled transfer.
--     * Slot: payerReceiver_id Description: Represents the parties to the transfer and their role.
--     * Slot: quantity_id Description: Represents the amount of the asset to be transferred. The cashflow amount is always a positive number, as the cashflow direction is implied by the payer/receiver attribute.
--     * Slot: asset_id Description: Represents the object that is subject to the transfer, it could be an asset or a reference.
--     * Slot: settlementDate_id Description: Represents the date on which the transfer to due.
--     * Slot: paymentDiscounting_id Description: FpML specifies the FpML PaymentDiscounting.model group for representing the discounting elements that can be associated with a payment.
-- # Class: ScheduledTransfer Description: A scheduled transfer built into the contract.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: transferType Description: Specifies the type of scheduled transfer.
--     * Slot: corporateActionTransferType
--     * Slot: payoutReference_id Description: Represents the origin to the transfer as a reference for lineage purposes, whether it originated from trade level settlement terms or from payment terms on an economic payout.
--     * Slot: payerReceiver_id Description: Represents the parties to the transfer and their role.
--     * Slot: quantity_id Description: Represents the amount of the asset to be transferred. The cashflow amount is always a positive number, as the cashflow direction is implied by the payer/receiver attribute.
--     * Slot: asset_id Description: Represents the object that is subject to the transfer, it could be an asset or a reference.
--     * Slot: settlementDate_id Description: Represents the date on which the transfer to due.
--     * Slot: paymentDiscounting_id Description: FpML specifies the FpML PaymentDiscounting.model group for representing the discounting elements that can be associated with a payment.
-- # Class: TransferBase Description: Defines the movement of an Asset (eg cash, securities or commodities) between two parties on a date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: payerReceiver_id Description: Represents the parties to the transfer and their role.
--     * Slot: quantity_id Description: Represents the amount of the asset to be transferred. The cashflow amount is always a positive number, as the cashflow direction is implied by the payer/receiver attribute.
--     * Slot: asset_id Description: Represents the object that is subject to the transfer, it could be an asset or a reference.
--     * Slot: settlementDate_id Description: Represents the date on which the transfer to due.
--     * Slot: paymentDiscounting_id Description: FpML specifies the FpML PaymentDiscounting.model group for representing the discounting elements that can be associated with a payment.
-- # Class: TradeIdentifier Description: Defines a trade identifier as a special case of the generic identifier type, that also includes the trade identifier class.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: The enumerated classification of the identifier. Optional as a trade identifier may be party-specific, in which case it may not correspond to any established classification.
--     * Slot: issuer Description: The identifier issuer, when specified explicitly alongside the identifier value (instead of being specified by reference to a party).
--     * Slot: ExecutionInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: ExerciseInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: PartyChangeInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Trade_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: issuerReference_id Description: The identifier issuer, when specified by reference to a party specified as part of the transaction.
-- # Class: PositionIdentifier Description: Defines a position identifier as a special case of the generic identifier type, that also includes the position identifier class.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: The enumerated classification of the identifier. Optional as a position identifier may be party-specific, in which case it may not correspond to any established classification.
--     * Slot: issuer Description: The identifier issuer, when specified explicitly alongside the identifier value (instead of being specified by reference to a party).
--     * Slot: CounterpartyPosition_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: issuerReference_id Description: The identifier issuer, when specified by reference to a party specified as part of the transaction.
-- # Class: Valuation Description: Defines the value of an investment, asset, or security
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: timestamp Description: Date and time of the last valuation marked to market, provided by the central counterparty (CCP) or calculated using the current or last available market price of the inputs.
--     * Slot: method Description: Method used for the valuation of the transaction by the valuation party.
--     * Slot: source Description: Source of the valuation of the transaction by the valuation party.
--     * Slot: scope Description:  Defines the scope of the valuation, what it applies to e.g. the collateral or the trade
--     * Slot: delta Description: The ratio of the change in the price of a derivative transaction to the change in the price of the underlying. This field is applicable only to options and swaptions.
--     * Slot: valuationTiming Description: Denotes when the valuation was sourced during a business day.
--     * Slot: TradeState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: CounterpartyPositionState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: amount_id Description: Current value of the outstanding contract
--     * Slot: priceComponent_id Description: Denotes the price used to compute the valuation.
-- # Class: Trade Description: Defines the output of a financial transaction between parties - a Business Event. A Trade impacts the financial position (i.e. the balance sheet) of involved parties.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: tradeDate Description: Specifies the date which the trade was agreed.
--     * Slot: clearedDate Description: Specifies the date on which a trade is cleared (novated) through a central counterparty clearing service.
--     * Slot: adjustment Description: Specifies the conditions that govern the adjustment to the quantity of a product being traded: e.g. execution, portfolio rebalancing etc. It is typically used in the context of Equity Swaps.
--     * Slot: Lineage_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: AggregationParameters_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: tradeTime_id Description: Denotes the trade time and timezone as agreed by the parties to the trade.
--     * Slot: executionDetails_id Description: Represents information specific to trades that arose from executions.
--     * Slot: contractDetails_id Description: Represents information specific to trades involving contractual products.
--     * Slot: collateral_id Description: Represents the collateral obligations of a party.
--     * Slot: product_id Description: The underlying product to be included in a contract or execution.
-- # Class: ExecutionDetails Description: Defines specific attributes that relate to trade executions.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: executionType Description: Identifies the type of execution, e.g. via voice, electronically...
--     * Slot: executionVenue_id Description: Represents the venue on which a trade was executed.
--     * Slot: packageReference_id Description: A reference to the package linking the trade with other trades, in case the trade was executed as part of a package (hence this attribute is optional).
-- # Class: ContractDetails Description: Defines specific attributes that relate to contractual details of trades.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: governingLaw Description: Represents the law governing the trade and associated contractual product terms.
-- # Class: Lineage Description: A class to provide lineage information across lifecycle events through a pointer or set of pointers into the event(s), contract(s) and, possibly, payout components that the event is dependent on or relates to. As an example, if an contractFormation event is corrected, the correction event will have a lineage into the initial event, which takes the form of a globalKey into that initial contract formation event. Two referencing mechanisms are provided as part of the CDM: either the globalKey, which corresponds to the hash value of the CDM class which is referred to, or a reference qualifier which is meant to provide support for the ingestion of xml documents with id/href mechanisms. The CDM recommends the use of the globalKey and provides a default implementation which is accessible in the generated code through org.isda.cdm.globalKey.GlobalKeyHashCalculator. If implementers want to use an alternative hashing mechanism, the API in which they need to plug it is com.rosetta.model.lib.HashFunction.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: StockSplitInstruction Description: Data required to perform a stock split business event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: adjustmentRatio Description: The number that denotes the cumulative quantity of post-split shares issued to shareholders versus the quantity of pre-split shares previously issued to shareholders.  This number will be multiplied by existing shares in an equity derivative contract or other positions to determine the post-split number of shares.  With regard to any reference to price, the pre-split reference price will be divided by this number to determine the post-split reference price.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The effective date of the stock split, also known as the ex-date. This is the date on which the additional shares are paid to the shareholders, or in the case of a reverse stock split, the number shares held by each shareholder is proportionally reduced.  Equity derivative transactions can be amended in firms' internal systems on such date.   In most markets, the listed stock price is reduced (or increased for a reverse stock split) to account for the split on the same date, but in some markets the price adjustment occurs on a later date.  In either case, equity derivative transactions should be amended on the date that the stocks are paid to the shareholders (or consolidated).
-- # Class: CreditEvent Description: Specifies the relevant data regarding a credit event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: creditEventType Description: The type of credit event taking place.
--     * Slot: eventDeterminationDate Description: The date in which the credit event is determined by the Credit Derivatives Determinations Comitee.
--     * Slot: auctionDate Description: The date on which the auction is scheduled to occur.
--     * Slot: recoveryPercent Description: The percentage of the original value of the asset affected by the credit event that can be recovered.
--     * Slot: finalPrice_id Description: The final price resulting from the auction.
--     * Slot: referenceInformation_id Description: The reference entity, part of a credit basket, impacted by the credit event.
-- # Class: CorporateAction Description: Specifies the relevant data regarding a corporate action
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: corporateActionType Description: The type of corporate action taking place.
--     * Slot: exDate Description: The date on which the corporate action is known to have taken place.
--     * Slot: payDate Description: The date on which resulting from the corporate action are delivered.
--     * Slot: recordDate Description: The date on which the account phyical balance and related underlier ownership is recorded by the custodian.
--     * Slot: announcementDate Description: The date on which the corporate action is announced by the issuer.
--     * Slot: bespokeEventDescription Description: Corporate action triggered by the occurrence of an event which description is seperatly agreed between the parties and/or described in any referenced agreement (for instance bespoke term described in any string type objects present in most root attributes of Agreement type).
--     * Slot: underlier_id Description: The underlier impacted by the corporate action.
--     * Slot: adjustmentFactor_id Description: Specifies any additional details e.g. further descriptions depending on the particular type of Corporate Action, adjustmentFactor, calculations
--     * Slot: informationSource_id Description: A class defining the source of data used in an Observation for any purposes. The data is either sourced from a Provider, or from a Party.
--     * Slot: dividendObservation_id Description: To record observations of dividends.
-- # Class: AdjustmentFactor Description: Describes the terms involved for adjusting the price of the underlier impacted by a Corporate Action.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value Description: The multiplier value applied to the price of the underlier impacted by a Corporate Action.
--     * Slot: calculationTerms_id Description: Describes the input terms involved in the calculation of the adjustment factor applied to the price of the underlier impacted by a Corporate Action.
-- # Class: AdjustmentFactorCalculationTerms Description: Describes the input terms involved in the calculation of the adjustment factor applied to the price of the underlier impacted by a Corporate Action.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: shareForShareRatio Description: Multiple value, say 'M/N' where 'M' is the number of shares after the event and 'N' is the number of shares prior to the event.
--     * Slot: shareForRightsRatio Description: Multiple value, say 'M/N' where 'M' is the number of rights after the event, and 'N' of shares prior to the event.
--     * Slot: dividendRatio Description: Multiplier value (e.g. 85 %, etc.) to calculate net dividend amount, given gross amount before taking into account the relevant fiscal features.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationFormula Description: To describe the formula used to calculate the Adjustment Factor.
--     * Slot: rightsSubscriptionPrice_id Description: The price to pay per each right.
--     * Slot: spinOff_id Description: Defines the underlier for both the Parent Company and the Child Compagny involved in Spin Off corporate action, as well as the respective price observation for each.
--     * Slot: merger_id Description: Defines the underlier for both the Purchaser Company and the Acquired Compagny involved in Spin Off corporate action, as well as the respective price observation for each.
--     * Slot: accrualFactor_id Description: The accrual rate and related terms, to adjust the price of an underlier impacted by a Corporate Action when economic impact consists in freezing the underlier price to last fixing and applying accruals for each remaining underlier price fixing date required i.e. for each, adjustedPrice = lastFixingPrice x (1 + accrualRate x DCF).
--     * Slot: lastFixingPriceBeforeAdjustment_id Description: The last fixing price of the Underlier affected by the CorporateAction, before any adjustment with regards to the CorporateAction.
--     * Slot: dividendObservation_id Description: To record observations of dividends.
-- # Class: AccrualFactor Description: The accrual rate and related terms, to adjust the price of an underlier impacted by a Corporate Action when economic impact consists in freezing the underlier price to the last fixing then applying accruals per each remaining underlier price fixing date required i.e. for each fixing date, adjustedPrice = lastFixingPrice x accrualFactor, where: accrualFactor = (1 + accrualRateValue x DCF).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: value_id Description: The rate to be applied to the last fixing price, for price accrual calculation purposes. DatedValue may be used for the purpose of representing Price series if such calculation is required for multiple dates.
--     * Slot: calculationTerms_id Description: Describes the input terms involved in the calculation of the accrual factor.
-- # Class: AccrualFactorCalculationTerms Description: Describes the input terms involved in the calculation of the accrual factor. Optionnally, long and short stub interpolation rates can be specified.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: tenorTillMaturity Description: The duration between last fixing date and the payment date of accruals, calculated in accordance with the appropriate DayCountFraction.
--     * Slot: dayCountFraction Description: The enumerated values to specify the day count fraction.
--     * Slot: interpolationTerms_id Description: Describes the rate, tenor, period duration for the short and long stubs, when the accrualRate optionnaly results from an interpolation method.
-- # Class: SpinOff Description: Defines the underlier for both the Parent Company and the Child Compagny involved in Spin Off corporate action, as well as th respective price observation for each.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: parentSecurity_id Description: Defines the underlier for the Parent Company involved in Spin Off corporate action.
--     * Slot: parentSecurityPrice_id Description: The price observation that relates to underlier for the Parent Company.
--     * Slot: childSecurity_id Description: Defines the underlier for the Child Company involved in Spin Off corporate action.
--     * Slot: childSecurityPrice_id Description: The price observation that relates to underlier for the Child Company.
-- # Class: Merger Description: Defines the underlier for both the Purchaser Company and the Acquired Compagny involved in Merger corporate action, as well as th respective price observation for each.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: purchaserSecurity_id Description: Defines the underlier for the Purchaser Company involved in Merger corporate action.
--     * Slot: purchaserSecurityPrice_id Description: The price observation that relates to underlier for the Purchaser Company.
--     * Slot: acquiredSecurity_id Description: Defines the underlier for the Acquired Company involved in Merger corporate action.
--     * Slot: acquiredSecurityPrice_id Description: The price observation that relates to underlier for the Acquired Company.
-- # Class: ClearingInstruction Description: All information required to perform the clear life cycle event; the clearing party (CCP), the two parties facing each other on the alpha contract, and optionally the parties acting as clearing members.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isOpenOffer Description: Open Offer
--     * Slot: alphaContract_id Description: The contract that will be submitted to the clearing house for clearing. The contract should indicate that it should be cleared by assigning a clearing organisation as a party role.
--     * Slot: clearingParty_id Description: The Central Counter party (CCP) that the contract will be submitted to for clearing.
--     * Slot: party1_id Description: First party facing the CCP if it is clearing for its own account.
--     * Slot: party2_id Description: Second party facing the CCP if it is clearing for its own account.
--     * Slot: clearerParty1_id Description: Optional party facing the CCP, acting as clearing member for party1.
--     * Slot: clearerParty2_id Description: Optional party facing the CCP, acting as clearing member for party2.
-- # Class: ExerciseEvent Description: A data defining:  the adjusted dates associated with a particular exercise event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: adjustedExerciseDate Description: The date on which the option exercise takes place. This date should already be adjusted for any applicable business day convention.
--     * Slot: adjustedRelevantSwapEffectiveDate Description: The effective date of the underlying swap associated with a given exercise date. This date should already be adjusted for any applicable business day convention.
--     * Slot: adjustedCashSettlementValuationDate Description: The date by which the cash settlement amount must be agreed. This date should already be adjusted for any applicable business day convention.
--     * Slot: adjustedCashSettlementPaymentDate Description: The date on which the cash settlement amount is paid. This date should already be adjusted for any applicable business day convention.
--     * Slot: adjustedExerciseFeePaymentDate Description: The date on which the exercise fee amount is paid. This date should already be adjusted for any applicable business day convention.
-- # Class: ReturnInstruction Description: Specifies the information required to create the return of a Security Finance Transaction.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: SecurityLendingInvoice Description: Specifies the information required for inclusion in a securities lending billing invoice.
