--     * Slot: summaryTransfer_id Description: The settlement terms for the billing summary
-- # Class: TradePricingReport Description: The attributes that are specific for consensus based pricing reporting.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: discountingIndex Description: It specifies the interest payable on collateral delivered under a CSA covering the trade.
--     * Slot: trade_id Description: Represents the cosensus based pricing parameters on a trade basis.
--     * Slot: pricingTime_id Description: The regional exchange close time for the underlying contract,including time zone, at which the trades should be priced. This provides an indication for which regional snapshot should be used for pricing primarily for Global markets where there are multiple regional close times.
-- # Class: MarginCallBase Description: Represents common attributes required for Issuance and Response to a Margin Call action as a result of a demand for delivery or return of collateral determined under a legal agreement such as a credit support document or equivalent.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: regMarginType Description: Identifies margin type and if related regulatory mandate
--     * Slot: regIMRole Description: Indicates the role of the party in an regulatory initial margin call instruction (i.e Pledgor party or Secured party).
--     * Slot: instructionType_id Description: Identifies the enumeration values to specify the call notification type, direction, specific action type.
--     * Slot: clearingBroker_id Description: Indicates the name of the Clearing Broker FCM/DCM.
--     * Slot: callIdentifier_id Description: Represents a unique Identifier for a margin call message, that can be referenced throughout all points of the process.
--     * Slot: callAgreementType_id Description: Specifies the legal agreement type the margin call is generated from and governed by.
--     * Slot: agreementMinimumTransferAmount_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement minimum transfer amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementThreshold_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement threshold amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementRounding_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement rounding in base currency.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyExposure_id Description: Represents the current mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency), to be referenced in a margin call.
--     * Slot: collateralPortfolio_id Description: Represents attributes to define the details of collateral assets within a collateral portfolio to be used in margin call messaging and contribute to collateral balances e.g securities in a collateral account recorded by the principal as held or posted.
--     * Slot: independentAmountBalance_id Description: Represents additional credit support amount over and above mark to market value.
-- # Class: Exposure Description: Represents the current mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: calculationDateTime Description: Indicates the date when the exposure is calculated if different from valuation date.
--     * Slot: valuationDateTime Description: Indicates the valuation date of the exposure underlying the calculation.
--     * Slot: tradePortfolio_id Description: Represents a Portfolio that describes all the positions held at a given time, in various states which can be either traded, settled, etc., with lineage information to the previous state.
--     * Slot: aggregateValue_id Description: Represents the aggregate value of the portfolio in base currency.
-- # Class: MarginCallExposure Description: Represents attributes required for mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: regMarginType Description: Identifies margin type and if related regulatory mandate
--     * Slot: regIMRole Description: Indicates the role of the party in an regulatory initial margin call instruction (i.e Pledgor party or Secured party).
--     * Slot: overallExposure_id Description: Represents the whole overall mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency).
--     * Slot: simmIMExposure_id Description: Represents Initial Margin (IM) exposure derived from ISDA SIMM calculation.
--     * Slot: scheduleGridIMExposure_id Description: Represents Initial Margin (IM) exposure derived from schedule or Grid calculation.
--     * Slot: instructionType_id Description: Identifies the enumeration values to specify the call notification type, direction, specific action type.
--     * Slot: clearingBroker_id Description: Indicates the name of the Clearing Broker FCM/DCM.
--     * Slot: callIdentifier_id Description: Represents a unique Identifier for a margin call message, that can be referenced throughout all points of the process.
--     * Slot: callAgreementType_id Description: Specifies the legal agreement type the margin call is generated from and governed by.
--     * Slot: agreementMinimumTransferAmount_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement minimum transfer amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementThreshold_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement threshold amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementRounding_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement rounding in base currency.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyExposure_id Description: Represents the current mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency), to be referenced in a margin call.
--     * Slot: collateralPortfolio_id Description: Represents attributes to define the details of collateral assets within a collateral portfolio to be used in margin call messaging and contribute to collateral balances e.g securities in a collateral account recorded by the principal as held or posted.
--     * Slot: independentAmountBalance_id Description: Represents additional credit support amount over and above mark to market value.
-- # Class: CollateralBalance Description: Represents common attributes to define a collateral balance recorded by the principal as held or posted.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: collateralBalanceStatus Description: Defines the collateral balance breakdown of settlement status.
--     * Slot: haircutIndicator Description: Indicates if the collateral balance amount is based on pre or post haircut, if a haircut is associated with the collateral asset
--     * Slot: CollateralPortfolio_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: amountBaseCurrency_id Description: Specifies the collateral balance amount in base currency determined within a collateral legal agreement, or defined for reporting purposes.
--     * Slot: payerReceiver_id Description: Specifies each of the parties in the collateral balance and its perspective with regards to the direction of the collateral balance, posted or received.
-- # Class: CollateralPortfolio Description: Represents common attributes to define the details of collateral assets, to be used in margin call messaging and contribute to collateral balances e.g securities in a collateral account.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: portfolioIdentifier_id Description: Specifies a unique identifier for a set of collateral positions in a portfolio.
--     * Slot: legalAgreement_id Description:  The specification of a legal agreement between two parties governing the collateral relationship such as Credit Support Agreement or Collateral Transfer Agreement etc. (NB: this can be provided by reference to a global key for each LegalAgreement object).
-- # Class: CollateralPosition Description: Specifies the individual components of collateral positions.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: collateralPositionStatus Description: Indicates the collateral positions settlement status.
--     * Slot: CollateralPortfolio_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: MarginCallResponseAction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: treatment_id Description: Specifies if there is any treatment to be applied to collateral, such as percentage discount which will impact collateral value.
--     * Slot: product_id Description: The product underlying the position.
--     * Slot: asset_id Description: The asset that underlies the position.
--     * Slot: cashBalance_id Description: The aggregate cost of proceeds.
--     * Slot: tradeReference_id Description: Reference to the Contract, in case product is contractual and the contract has been formed.
-- # Class: MarginCallIssuance Description: Represents common attributes required for a Margin Call Issuance under a legal agreement such as a credit support document or equivalent.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: regMarginType Description: Identifies margin type and if related regulatory mandate
--     * Slot: regIMRole Description: Indicates the role of the party in an regulatory initial margin call instruction (i.e Pledgor party or Secured party).
--     * Slot: callAmountInBaseCurrency_id Description: Specifies the amount of margin being called for which accounts for margin calculation inclusive of exposure, independent amount,threshold,collateral balance, MTA, rounding increments (in base currency detailed in supporting collateral agreement).
--     * Slot: instructionType_id Description: Identifies the enumeration values to specify the call notification type, direction, specific action type.
--     * Slot: clearingBroker_id Description: Indicates the name of the Clearing Broker FCM/DCM.
--     * Slot: callIdentifier_id Description: Represents a unique Identifier for a margin call message, that can be referenced throughout all points of the process.
--     * Slot: callAgreementType_id Description: Specifies the legal agreement type the margin call is generated from and governed by.
--     * Slot: agreementMinimumTransferAmount_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement minimum transfer amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementThreshold_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement threshold amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementRounding_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement rounding in base currency.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyExposure_id Description: Represents the current mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency), to be referenced in a margin call.
--     * Slot: collateralPortfolio_id Description: Represents attributes to define the details of collateral assets within a collateral portfolio to be used in margin call messaging and contribute to collateral balances e.g securities in a collateral account recorded by the principal as held or posted.
--     * Slot: independentAmountBalance_id Description: Represents additional credit support amount over and above mark to market value.
-- # Class: MarginCallInstructionType Description: Represents enumeration values to specify the call notification type, direction, specific action type.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: callType Description: Indicates the status of the call message type, such as expected call, notification of a call or an actionable margin call.
--     * Slot: visibilityIndicator Description: Indicates the choice if the call instruction is visible or not to the other party.
-- # Class: MarginCallResponseAction Description: Specifies the margin call action details, including collateral to be moved and its direction.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: marginCallAction Description: Specifies the margin call action details, specified as either Delivery or Return.
--     * Slot: MarginCallResponse_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MarginCallResponse Description: Represents common attributes required for a Margin Call Response under a legal agreement such as a credit support document or equivalent.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: marginResponseType Description: Indicates the response type, such as, is the margin call response a 'full' 'part' agreement or 'dispute'.
--     * Slot: regMarginType Description: Identifies margin type and if related regulatory mandate
--     * Slot: regIMRole Description: Indicates the role of the party in an regulatory initial margin call instruction (i.e Pledgor party or Secured party).
--     * Slot: agreedAmountBaseCurrency_id Description: Indicates the amount that posting entity agrees to remit in response to margin call (in base currency).
--     * Slot: instructionType_id Description: Identifies the enumeration values to specify the call notification type, direction, specific action type.
--     * Slot: clearingBroker_id Description: Indicates the name of the Clearing Broker FCM/DCM.
--     * Slot: callIdentifier_id Description: Represents a unique Identifier for a margin call message, that can be referenced throughout all points of the process.
--     * Slot: callAgreementType_id Description: Specifies the legal agreement type the margin call is generated from and governed by.
--     * Slot: agreementMinimumTransferAmount_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement minimum transfer amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementThreshold_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement threshold amount in base currency.
--     * Slot: agreementRounding_id Description: Specifies the collateral legal agreement rounding in base currency.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyExposure_id Description: Represents the current mark to market value or IM calculation value of the trade portfolio as recorded by the principle (in base currency), to be referenced in a margin call.
--     * Slot: collateralPortfolio_id Description: Represents attributes to define the details of collateral assets within a collateral portfolio to be used in margin call messaging and contribute to collateral balances e.g securities in a collateral account recorded by the principal as held or posted.
--     * Slot: independentAmountBalance_id Description: Represents additional credit support amount over and above mark to market value.
-- # Class: ClosedState Description:  A class to qualify the closed state of an execution or a contract through the combination or a state (e.g. terminated, novated) and a set of dates: activity date, effective date and, when relevant, last payment date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: state Description: The qualification of what gave way to the contract or execution closure, e.g. allocation, termination, ...
--     * Slot: activityDate Description: The activity date on which the closing state took place, i.e. either the event date of the closing event (e.g. option exercise, contract early termination) or the contractual termination date.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The date on which the closing event contractually takes effect, when different from the activity date. When an explicit event effective date attribute is associated with the closing event, it will be that date. In the case of a cancellation event, it will be the date on which the cancelled event took place.
--     * Slot: lastPaymentDate Description: The date associated with the last payment in relation to the artefact (e.g. contract) to which this closed state applies. As an example, in the case of an early termination event, it would be the settlement date of the associated fee, if applicable.
-- # Abstract Class: Transfer Description: The type of transfer.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: ContractBase Description: Encapsulates data features common to trade and position.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: contractDetails_id Description: Represents information specific to trades or positions involving contractual products.
--     * Slot: executionDetails_id Description: Defines specific attributes that relate to trade or position executions.
--     * Slot: collateral_id Description: Represents the collateral obligations of a party.
-- # Class: CounterpartyPosition Description: A Position describes the accumulated effect of a set of securities or financial transactions.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: openDateTime Description: The date and time when the position was opened.
--     * Slot: positionBase_id Description: Encapsulates the core constituents that characterize a position.
--     * Slot: contractDetails_id Description: Represents information specific to trades or positions involving contractual products.
--     * Slot: executionDetails_id Description: Defines specific attributes that relate to trade or position executions.
--     * Slot: collateral_id Description: Represents the collateral obligations of a party.
-- # Class: PositionBase Description: Base class to describe a Position, which could be a group of products (e.g. trade portfolio) or a group of assets (e.g. collateral portfolio).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: product_id Description: The product underlying the position.
--     * Slot: asset_id Description: The asset that underlies the position.
--     * Slot: cashBalance_id Description: The aggregate cost of proceeds.
--     * Slot: tradeReference_id Description: Reference to the Contract, in case product is contractual and the contract has been formed.
-- # Class: Position Description: A Position describes how much of a given Product is being held and constitutes the atomic element of a Portfolio.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: PortfolioState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: product_id Description: The product underlying the position.
--     * Slot: asset_id Description: The asset that underlies the position.
--     * Slot: cashBalance_id Description: The aggregate cost of proceeds.
--     * Slot: tradeReference_id Description: Reference to the Contract, in case product is contractual and the contract has been formed.
-- # Class: PortfolioState Description: State-full representation of a Portfolio that describes all the positions held at a given time, in various states which can be either traded, settled, etc., with lineage information to the previous state
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: Lineage_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: lineage_id Description: Pointer to the previous PortfolioState and new Event(s) leading to the current (new) state. Previous PortfolioState in the Lineage can be Null in case this is the start of the chain of Events.
-- # Class: AggregationParameters Description:  Parameters to be used to filter events that are relevant to a given portfolio in order to calculate the state of this portfolio. The attributes correspond to all the possible aggregation criteria that can be used and these criteria can be combined. All the attributes are optional.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: dateTime Description: To aggregate as of a particular date
--     * Slot: totalPosition Description: Specifies whether to calculate total position to given date, or only daily position for the given date.
--     * Slot: positionStatus Description: To aggregate based on position status (EXECUTED, SETTLED etc)
-- # Class: Portfolio Description:  A Portfolio represents an aggregation of multiple Positions, by describing the parameters that this Portfolio should be aggregated based on. The resulting PortfolioState is calculated using these aggregation parameters as inputs, by aggregating all the Events that are relevant to this Portfolio. The concept of Portfolio works at all levels in the model: from the highest for a given LegalEntity for instance, to the lowest to account for security substitutions in a secutity financing transaction. As such, Portfolio can be used either above or below the Contract level.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: aggregationParameters_id Description: Describes the portfolio by describing how to aggregate all its relevant Events.
--     * Slot: portfolioState_id Description: Describes the state of the Portfolio as a list of Positions resulting from the aggregation.
-- # Class: Inventory Description: A data type that can be used to describe an inventory of securities.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: InventoryRecord Description: An individual piece of inventory. This represents a single security.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: Inventory_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: identifer_id Description: Unique identifier for this record. This can be used to uniquely identify a specific piece of inventory.
--     * Slot: security_id Description: The security details.
-- # Class: AvailableInventory Description: A data type that can be used to describe the inventory of securities that a party holds. The securities are held in the AvailableInventoryRecord, with each item in the array being an individual security and its associated criteria. Criteria can include the quantity available, the rate at which the security is available to borrow at, as well as other details that can affect the decision as to whether a party wants to utilise the securities listed.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: availableInventoryType Description: Defines the purpose of this inventory.
--     * Slot: messageInformation_id Description: Allows details related to the availability messaging use case to be defined
-- # Class: AvailableInventoryRecord Description: An individual piece of available inventory. This represents a single security and its associated criteria. The criteria are used to describe any restrictions on the securities.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: expirationDateTime Description: There may be a set period/time restriction associated to the security.
--     * Slot: AvailableInventory_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: SecurityLocate_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: quantity_id Description: The quantity of the security
--     * Slot: interestRate_id Description: An optional element which can be used to hold a rate associated to this piece of availability.
--     * Slot: identifer_id Description: Unique identifier for this record. This can be used to uniquely identify a specific piece of inventory.
--     * Slot: security_id Description: The security details.
-- # Class: SecurityLocate Description: A locate is an approval from a broker that needs to be obtained prior to effecting a short sale in an equity security. Similar to security availability, a borrower can request a single or multiple securities, but at least one must be requested.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: availableInventoryType Description: Defines the purpose of this inventory.
--     * Slot: messageInformation_id Description: Allows details related to the availability messaging use case to be defined
-- # Class: CreditLimitInformation Description: A class to represent the credit limit utilisation information.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CreditLimitUtilisation Description: Credit limit utilisation breakdown by executed trades and pending orders.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: executed_id Description: Credit limit utilisation attributable to executed trades.
--     * Slot: pending_id Description: Credit limit utilisation attributable to pending unexecuted orders.
-- # Class: CreditLimitUtilisationPosition
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: shortPosition Description: Credit limit utilisation attributable to short positions.
--     * Slot: longPosition Description: Credit limit utilisation attributable to long positions.
--     * Slot: global_ Description: Global credit limit utilisation amount, agnostic of long/short position direction.
-- # Class: CustomisedWorkflow Description: In its initial iteration, this class is meant to support the DTCC TIW workflow information.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: itemName Description: In this initial iteration, this corresponds to the DTCC TIW element name.
--     * Slot: itemValue Description: In this initial iteration, this corresponds to the DTCC value.
--     * Slot: PartyCustomisedWorkflow_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: WorkflowStepApproval Description: Party approvals associated to the current WorkflowStep.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: approved Description: Flag denoting whether the workflow step is approved or not
--     * Slot: rejectedReason Description: Optional reason for rejecting the workflow step
--     * Slot: WorkflowStep_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: party_id Description: Reference to the Party who is approving/rejecting this workflow step
--     * Slot: timestamp_id Description: Timestamp of the approval
-- # Class: WorkflowStep Description: A workflow step represents the state of a business event. The workflow step contains a reference to a previous WorkflowStep in order to preserve lineage. A workflow step is accepted if it contains a business event, proposed if proposedEvent is present and is rejected if the rejected flag is set.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: rejected Description: Flags this step as rejected.
--     * Slot: action Description: Specifies whether the event is a new, a correction or a cancellation.
--     * Slot: Lineage_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: Workflow_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: businessEvent_id Description: Life cycle event for the step.
--     * Slot: counterpartyPositionBusinessEvent_id Description: Documents the life cycle event for a position.
--     * Slot: proposedEvent_id Description: The proposed event for a workflow step.
--     * Slot: previousWorkflowStep_id Description: Optional previous workflow step that provides lineage to workflow steps that precedes it.
--     * Slot: nextEvent_id Description: The intended next event can be specified, even if the instructions are not known yet.
--     * Slot: messageInformation_id Description: Contains all information pertaining the FpML messaging header
--     * Slot: lineage_id Description: The lineage attribute provides a linkage among lifecycle events through the globalKey hash value. One example is when a given lifecycle event is being corrected or cancelled. In such case, each subsequent event will have lineage into the prior version of that event. The second broad use case is when an event has a dependency upon either another event (e.g. the regular payment associated with a fix/float swap will have a lineage into the reset event, which will in turn have a lineage into the observation event for the floating rate and the contract) or a contract (e.g. the exercise of an option has a lineage into that option).
--     * Slot: creditLimitInformation_id
--     * Slot: workflowState_id Description: The event workflow information, i.e. the workflow status, the associated comment and the partyCustomisedWorkflow which purpose is to provide the ability to associate custom workflow information to the CDM.
-- # Class: Workflow Description: A collection of workflow steps which together make up an entire workflow sequence.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: EventInstruction Description: Specifies instructions to create a BusinessEvent.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: intent Description: The intent attribute is meant to be specified when the event qualification cannot be programmatically inferred from the event features. As a result it is only associated with those primitives that can give way to such ambiguity, the quantityChange being one of those. An example of such is a reduction in the trade notional, which could be interpreted as either a trade correction (unless a maximum period of time post-event is specified as part of the qualification), a partial termination or a portfolio rebalancing in the case of an equity swap. On the other hand, an event such as the exercise is not expected to have an associated intent as there should not be ambiguity.
--     * Slot: corporateActionIntent Description: The intent of a corporate action on the position.
--     * Slot: eventDate Description: Specifies the date on which the event is taking place. This date is equal to the trade date in the case of a simple execution.  However it can be different from the trade date, for example in the case of a partial termination.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The date on which the event contractually takes effect, when different from the event date.
--     * Slot: eventTime_id Description: The time and zone of the date in which the event is taking place.
--     * Slot: effectiveTime_id Description: The time and zone of the date in which the event contractually takes effect.
--     * Slot: packageInformation_id Description: Specifies the package information in case the business event represents several trades executed as a package (hence this attribute is optional). The package information is only instantiated once at the business event level to preserve referential integrity, whereas individual trades make reference to it to identify that they are part of a package.
-- # Class: EventTimestamp Description: A class to represent the various set of timestamps that can be associated with lifecycle events, as a collection of [dateTime, qualifier].
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: dateTime Description: The CDM specifies that the zoned date time is to be expressed in accordance with ISO 8601, either as UTC as an offset to UTC.
--     * Slot: qualification Description: The timestamp qualifier is specified through an enumeration because the experience of integrating the DTCC and CME data representations suggests that a wide set of timestamps are currently utilized among service providers, while there is not at present an objective set of criteria that could help suggest a defined set of timestamps as part of the CDM. At some future point, one possible baseline could be developed from the review of the set of timestamps specified across regulatory regimes and regulations (incl. regulations such as high frequency trading). Also, the integration with a further set of implementations and the specification of business workflows such as clearing as part of the CDM development should help confirm the implementation approach in this respect.
-- # Class: WorkflowState Description: A class to specify workflow information, which is conceptually applicable to all lifecycle events.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: workflowStatus Description: The workflow status indicator, e.g. Accepted, Rejected, ...
--     * Slot: comment Description: A comment field to be associated with the workflow, e.g. to specify why a transaction event was rejected by a party.
--     * Slot: warehouseIdentity Description: The identity of the warehouse, if any, that is executing that workflow step.
-- # Class: LimitApplicable
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: limitType Description: Standard code to indicate which type of credit line is being referred to - i.e. IM, DV01, PV01, CS01, Notional, Clip Size, Notional, maximumOrderQuantity.
--     * Slot: clipSize Description: This element is required in FpML, optional in CDM for the purpose of accommodating the CME data representation while making reference to the FpML one.
--     * Slot: amountUtilized Description: The limit utilised by all the cleared trades for the limit level and limit type. While the attribute is of type integer in FpML and the CME schema, it has been specified to be of type number in the CDM to take into consideration java size limits as well as for consistency purposes with the way most monetary amounts are expressed.
--     * Slot: amountRemaining Description: The limit remaining for the limit level and limit type. This does not take into account any pending trades. While the attribute is of type integer in FpML and the CME schema, it has been specified to be of type number in the CDM to take into consideration java size limits as well as for consistency purposes with the way most monetary amounts are expressed.
--     * Slot: currency Description: The currency in which the applicable limit is denominated. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
--     * Slot: utilization_id
--     * Slot: velocity_id
-- # Class: LimitApplicableExtended Description: A class to represent the CDM attributes that are not part of the FpML standard. Once broader usage is confirmed, it is expected that those two classes can be collapsed.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: limitLevel Description: The level at which the limit is set: customer business, proprietary business or account level. This attribute is specified as a string as part of the CME clearing confirmation specification.
--     * Slot: limitAmount Description: The total limit available for the limit level and limit type. While the attribute is of type integer in the CME schema, it has been specified to be of type number in the CDM to take into consideration java size limits as well as for consistency purposes with the way most monetary amounts are expressed.
--     * Slot: limitImpactDueToTrade Description: The limit utilized by this specific trade. While the attribute is of type integer in the CME schema, it has been specified to be of type number in the CDM to take into consideration java size limits as well as for consistency purposes with the way most monetary amounts are expressed.
--     * Slot: limitType Description: Standard code to indicate which type of credit line is being referred to - i.e. IM, DV01, PV01, CS01, Notional, Clip Size, Notional, maximumOrderQuantity.
--     * Slot: clipSize Description: This element is required in FpML, optional in CDM for the purpose of accommodating the CME data representation while making reference to the FpML one.
--     * Slot: amountUtilized Description: The limit utilised by all the cleared trades for the limit level and limit type. While the attribute is of type integer in FpML and the CME schema, it has been specified to be of type number in the CDM to take into consideration java size limits as well as for consistency purposes with the way most monetary amounts are expressed.
--     * Slot: amountRemaining Description: The limit remaining for the limit level and limit type. This does not take into account any pending trades. While the attribute is of type integer in FpML and the CME schema, it has been specified to be of type number in the CDM to take into consideration java size limits as well as for consistency purposes with the way most monetary amounts are expressed.
--     * Slot: currency Description: The currency in which the applicable limit is denominated. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
--     * Slot: CreditLimitInformation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: utilization_id
--     * Slot: velocity_id
-- # Class: MessageInformation Description: This class corresponds to the components of the FpML MessageHeader.model.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: messageId Description: A unique identifier assigned to the message.
--     * Slot: sentBy Description: The identifier for the originator of a message instance.
-- # Class: PartyCustomisedWorkflow Description: A class to specify a party-related, non-standardized data in a generic form.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: partyName Description: The party name to which the workflow pertains to.
--     * Slot: WorkflowState_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: partyReference_id Description: Reference to the party to which the workflow pertains to.
-- # Class: Velocity
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: periodMultiplier Description: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2, or 3. If the period value is T (Term) then period multiplier must contain the value 1.
--     * Slot: period Description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month, year or term of the stream.
-- # Class: ContractualMatrix
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: matrixType Description: Identifies the form of applicable matrix.
--     * Slot: matrixTerm Description: Defines any applicable key into the relevant matrix. For example, the Transaction Type would be the single term required for the Credit Derivatives Physical Settlement Matrix. This element should be omitted in the case of the 2000 ISDA Definitions Settlement Matrix for Early Termination and Swaptions.
--     * Slot: AgreementName_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: ContractualTermsSupplement Description: A contractual supplement (such as those published by ISDA) and its publication date that will apply to the trade.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: contractualTermsSupplementType Description: Identifies the form of applicable contractual supplement.
--     * Slot: publicationDate Description: Specifies the publication date of the applicable version of the contractual supplement.
--     * Slot: AgreementName_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: OtherAgreement Description: A class for defining an agreement executed between parties.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: An identifier that has been created to identify the agreement.
--     * Slot: otherAgreementType Description: The agreement executed between the parties and intended to govern product-specific derivatives transactions between those parties.
--     * Slot: version Description: The version of the agreement.
--     * Slot: date Description: The date on which the agreement was signed.
-- # Class: Resource Description: Describes the resource that contains the media representation of a business event (i.e used for stating the Publicly Available Information). For example, can describe a file or a URL that represents the event. This type is an extended version of a type defined by RIXML (www.rixml.org).  Rosetta restricts the FpML implementation by not providing the ability to associated a document in hexadecimalBinary or base64Binary until such time that actual use cases will come up.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: resourceId Description: The unique identifier of the resource within the event. FpML specifies this element of type resourceIdScheme but with no specified value.
--     * Slot: resourceType Description: A description of the type of the resource, e.g. a confirmation.
--     * Slot: language Description: Indicates the language of the resource, described using the ISO 639-2/T Code.
--     * Slot: sizeInBytes Description: Indicates the size of the resource in bytes. It could be used by the end user to estimate the download time and storage needs.
--     * Slot: mimeType Description: Indicates the type of media used to store the content. mimeType is used to determine the software product(s) that can read the content. MIME Types are described in RFC 2046.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the resource.  It is specified as a NormalizedString in FpML.
--     * Slot: comments Description: Any additional comments that are deemed necessary. For example, which software version is required to open the document? Or, how does this resource relate to the others for this event?
--     * Slot: string Description: Provides extra information as string. In case the extra information is in XML format, a CDATA section must be placed around the source message to prevent its interpretation as XML content.
--     * Slot: url Description: Indicates where the resource can be found, as a URL that references the information on a web server accessible to the message recipient.
--     * Slot: CreditEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreementBase_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: length_id Description: Indicates the length of the resource. For example, if the resource were a PDF file, the length would be in pages.
-- # Class: ResourceLength Description: A class to indicate the length of the resource.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: lengthUnit Description: The length unit of the resource. For example, pages (pdf, text documents) or time (audio, video files).
--     * Slot: lengthValue Description: The length value of the resource.
-- # Class: AgreementTerms Description: Specification of the content of a legal agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: clauseLibrary Description: Specification of whether the agreement terms have been negotiated using the clause library methodology.
--     * Slot: agreement_id Description: Specification of the standard set of terms that define a legal agreement.
-- # Class: LegalAgreement Description: The specification of a legal agreement between two parties, being negotiated or having been executed. This includes the baseline information and the optional specialised elections
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: agreementDate Description: The date on which the legal agreement has been agreed between the parties. This corresponds to the Date of Deed in an English Law document.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The date on which, or as of which, the agreement is effective, if different from the agreement date. It is expected that it will most often correspond to the agreement date, although there could be situations where the parties will explicitly agree on a distinct effective date.
--     * Slot: ContractFormationInstruction_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: ContractDetails_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: LegalAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: CreditSupportDocumentElection_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: agreementTerms_id Description: Specification of the content of the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: umbrellaAgreement_id Description: Specifies a set of legal entities which are part of a legal agreement beyond the two contracting parties to that agreement.
--     * Slot: legalAgreementIdentification_id Description: The type of legal agreement, identified via a set of composable attributes: agreementName, publisher, governing law and version, e.g. ISDA 2013 Standard Credit Support Annex English Law.
-- # Class: LegalAgreementBase Description: Specifies the legal agreement baseline information, being negotiated or having been executed. It excludes specialized elections
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: agreementDate Description: The date on which the legal agreement has been agreed between the parties. This corresponds to the Date of Deed in an English Law document.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate Description: The date on which, or as of which, the agreement is effective, if different from the agreement date. It is expected that it will most often correspond to the agreement date, although there could be situations where the parties will explicitly agree on a distinct effective date.
--     * Slot: legalAgreementIdentification_id Description: The type of legal agreement, identified via a set of composable attributes: agreementName, publisher, governing law and version, e.g. ISDA 2013 Standard Credit Support Annex English Law.
-- # Class: LegalAgreementIdentification Description: Specifies the type of legal agreement, identified via a set of composable attributes: agreementName, publisher, governing law and version, e.g. ISDA 2013 Standard Credit Support Annex English Law.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: governingLaw Description: The law governing the legal agreement, e.g. English Law, New York Law or Japanese Law.
--     * Slot: publisher Description: The legal agreement publisher, e.g. ISDA.
--     * Slot: vintage Description: In the case where successive definitions of the legal agreement have been developed, the vintage identification. This is typically (but not necessarily) done by referencing the year, e.g. 2013 in the case of the ISDA 2013 Standard Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: CreditSupportDocumentElection_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: agreementName_id Description: The legal agreement name, e.g. Credit Support Annex for Variation Margin.
-- # Class: AgreementName Description: Specifies the agreement name through an agreement type and optional detailed sub agreement type.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: agreementType Description: Specification of the legal agreement type.
--     * Slot: creditSupportAgreementType Description: Specification of the credit support agreement type.
--     * Slot: creditSupportAgreementMarginType Description: specifies the type of margin for which a legal agreement is named.
--     * Slot: masterAgreementType Description: Specification of the master agreement type.
--     * Slot: masterConfirmationType Description: The type of master confirmation executed between the parties.
--     * Slot: masterConfirmationAnnexType Description: The type of master confirmation annex executed between the parties.
--     * Slot: otherAgreement Description: Definition of an agreement that is not enumerated in the CDM.
--     * Slot: brokerConfirmationType
-- # Class: UmbrellaAgreement Description: Specifies the set of agreements, the parties of which are set within UmbrellaAgreementSet, beyond the two contracting parties to that agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: UmbrellaAgreementParty Description: Specifies the entities that are part of the umbrella agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: actingAs Description: Specifies the CounterpartyRoleEnum, e.g. either Party1 or Party2, that is associated to the party.
--     * Slot: partyRole Description: Represents the legal role that each defined entity to the agreement performs within the structure of that agreement.
--     * Slot: party_id Description: Specifies the party to the umbrella agreement
--     * Slot: nonLegalEntity_id Description: Specifies a non-legal entity that exists in the agreement with a defined relationship to a Legal entity to the agreement.
--     * Slot: parentParty_id Description: Represents the identification of a parent child relationship between two entities in the Umbrella agreement, allowing non-legal entities to be linked to the appropriate legal entity and allowing funds, portfolio or managed accounts to be linked to their applicable Investment Manager or Agent within the agreement.
-- # Class: NonLegalEntity Description: Specifies a non-legal entity that exists in the agreement with a defined relationship to a Legal entity to the agreement
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: Specifies the unique identifier value for a non-legal entity such as a sleeve, or sub account, that is a party to the agreement and has a relationship with a legal entity defined on the agreement.
--     * Slot: identifierType Description: Specifies the Identifier type for a non-Legal entity to the agreement, for example the use of an alert code to uniquely identify a non-Legal entity.
-- # Class: UmbrellaAgreementSet Description: Represents the groups of agreement term elections that exist within the agreement and to which entities that particular group of elections apply. Where all entities under the umbrella have the same set of elections only one agreement set will exist. At least one agreement set must be defined for an Umbrella agreement
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: Represents any additional language that may need to be captured regarding the structure or application of terms that may exist for the agreement.
--     * Slot: UmbrellaAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: agreement_id Description: Specification of the standard set of terms that define a legal agreement.
-- # Class: ContactInformationElection Description: Specifies the party reference and the associated contact information.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: partyReference Description: The party to which the election and details apply.
--     * Slot: primaryContactInformation_id Description: The main notice/address information of the party.
-- # Class: NoticeInformationElection Description: Specifies the party reference and the associated notice and contact information.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: partyReference Description: The party to which the election and details apply.
--     * Slot: DemandsAndNotices_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: primaryContactInformation_id Description: The main notice/address information of the party.
-- # Class: NoticeContactInformation Description: Specifies notice information including address and, optionally, an associated person. This type also supports the ISDA CSA representation as a single string, through the address attribute in Contact Information.
