--     * Slot: asCalculationAgent Description: If set to True, the Calculation Time for Initial Margin is the time as of which the Calculation Agent (IM) computes its end of day valuations of derivatives transactions.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationTimeTerms Description: Additional Terms applicable to Calculation Time for Initial Margin.
-- # Class: BespokeTransferTiming Description: A class to specify any bespoke Transfer Timing language by each party to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: A boolean flag to specify whether bespoke transfer terms are applicable or not.
--     * Slot: bespokeTransferTimingTerms Description: The bespoke transfer timing terms applicable to the agreement.
-- # Class: CalculationAgentTerms Description: Details of the party calculating the value of collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party which is specified as Calculation Agent for Initial Margin.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationAgentTerms Description: The Calculation Agent (IM) terms when specified.
-- # Class: CalculationAndTimingLegacy Description: Specification of the Calculation, Valuation and Timing terms specific to the Legacy (1994/95) Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: valuationDate_id Description: Details of the days on which calculations are to be made to determine the Delivery Amount and/or Return Amount.
--     * Slot: valuationTime_id Description: Specifies the time on which the value of collateral or exposure are calculated in accordance with the agreement.
--     * Slot: valuationAgent_id Description: Details of the party calculating the value of collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: The time by which a demand for the Transfer of Eligible Credit Support (IM) or Posted Credit Support (IM) needs to be made in order for the transfer to take place in accordance with the Transfer Timing provisions.
-- # Class: CalculationAndTimingVariationMargin Description: Specification of the Calculation, Valuation and Timing terms specific to the Variation Margin Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: valuationDate_id Description: Details of the days on which calculations are to be made to determine the Delivery Amount and/or Return Amount.
--     * Slot: valuationTime_id Description: Specifies the time on which the value of collateral or exposure are calculated in accordance with the agreement.
--     * Slot: valuationAgent_id Description: Details of the party valuating the collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: valuationDateLocation_id Description: The specified location where the credit exposure will be calculated by the respective parties.
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: The time by which a demand for the Transfer of Eligible Credit Support (IM) or Posted Credit Support (IM) needs to be made in order for the transfer to take place in accordance with the Transfer Timing provisions.
-- # Class: CalculationAndTimingInitialMargin Description: Specification of the Calculation, Valuation and Timing terms specific to the Initial Margin Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cashSettlementDay
--     * Slot: securitiesSettlementDay
--     * Slot: calculationAgentTerms_id Description: Details of the party calculating the value of collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationDate_id Description: The specification of bespoke Calculation Date terms for the purposes of Initial or Variation Margin by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationTime_id Description: Bespoke terms to describe the time as of which such party (or the Calculation Agent (IM) (if applicale)) computes its end of day valuations of derivatives transactions.
--     * Slot: calculationDateLocation_id Description: The specified location where the credit exposure will be calculated by the respective parties.
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: The time by which a demand for the Transfer of Eligible Credit Support (IM) or Posted Credit Support (IM) needs to be made in order for the transfer to take place in accordance with the Transfer Timing provisions.
-- # Class: CalculationAndTimingCollateralTransferAgreement Description: Specification of the Calculation, Valuation and Timing terms specific to the Initial Margin Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cashSettlementDay
--     * Slot: securitiesSettlementDay
--     * Slot: calculationAgentTerms_id Description: Details of the party calculating the value of collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationDate_id Description: The specification of bespoke Calculation Date terms for the purposes of Initial or Variation Margin by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: bespokeCalculationTime_id Description: Bespoke terms to describe the time as of which such party (or the Calculation Agent (IM) (if applicale)) computes its end of day valuations of derivatives transactions.
--     * Slot: calculationDateLocation_id Description: The specified location where the credit exposure will be calculated by the respective parties.
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: The time by which a demand for the Transfer of Eligible Credit Support (IM) or Posted Credit Support (IM) needs to be made in order for the transfer to take place in accordance with the Transfer Timing provisions.
-- # Class: CalculationAndTimingBase Description: A logical container designed to hold a set of related data. In this case, designed to hold a set of clauses that are common amongst Legacy (1994/95), Variation Margin and Initial Margin Credit Support Documents in regards to Calculation, Valuation and Timing terms.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: The time by which a demand for the Transfer of Eligible Credit Support (IM) or Posted Credit Support (IM) needs to be made in order for the transfer to take place in accordance with the Transfer Timing provisions.
-- # Class: CalculationCurrencyElection Description: A class to specify the ISDA SIMM Calculation Currency.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party which the SIMM Calculation Currency qualification applies to.
--     * Slot: isBaseCurrency Description: The SIMM Calculation Currency (also known as SIMM Reporting Currency) means the Base Currency when True. It means a different currency when False. In that latter case, the SIMM Calculation Currency is specified as part of the currency attribute.
--     * Slot: currency Description: The currency in which the ISDA SIMM Calculation is denominated, when different from the Base Currency. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
--     * Slot: SimmCalculationCurrency_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: ValuationCalculationDateLocation Description: Specification of the Calculation Date Location for the respective parties to the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: ValuationCalculationDateLocationElection Description: A class to specify each of the party elections with respect to the Calculation Date Location.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: businessCenter Description: The Calculation Date Location when specified as a business center which corresponds to the FpML list of business centers or can be mapped to it.
--     * Slot: customLocation Description: The Calculation Date Location when specified a location which doesn't correspond to the FpML list of business centers or cannot be mapped to it.
--     * Slot: ValuationCalculationDateLocation_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: CollateralAccessBreach Description: A class to specify Collateral Access Breach language.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: Collateral Access Breach terms are applicable when True and not applicable when False.
--     * Slot: cabEndDateElection Description: Determination of whether the Collateral Access Breach end date is a number of days (True) or specified (False).
--     * Slot: cabEndDate Description: The business days following the related Collateral Access Breach when the additional terms end.
--     * Slot: cabEndDateTerms Description: Specific terms for when Collateral Access Breach terms end.
-- # Class: CollateralManagementAgreement Description: A class to specify the Collateral Management Agreement election.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CollateralManagementAgreementElection Description: A class to specify the Collateral Management Agreement election.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: collateralManagementAgreement Description: The designated Collateral Management Agreement with respect to the elective party as the Obligee.
--     * Slot: CollateralManagementAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: CollateralRounding Description: A class to specify the rounding methodology applicable to the Delivery Amount and the Return Amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount Description: The nearest integral multiple of Base Currency units to which the Delivery Amount will be rounded in accordance with the specified rounding direction.
--     * Slot: deliveryDirection Description: The rounding rule applicable to the Delivery Amount (which can be (i) up to nearest; (ii) down to nearest).
--     * Slot: returnAmount Description: The nearest integral multiple of Base Currency units to which the Return Amount will be rounded in accordance with the specified rounding direction.
--     * Slot: returnDirection Description: The rounding rule applicable to the Return Amount (which can be (i) up to nearest; (ii) down to nearest).
--     * Slot: currency Description: The currency in which the Delivery Amount and Return Amount rounding amounts are specified.
--     * Slot: other Description: Utilised where the clause data structure is not able to capture a material aspect of the clause.
-- # Class: ConditionsPrecedent Description: A class to specify the two set of elections that may overwrite the default Condition Precedent provision.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: conditionsPrecedentElection Description: The election to specify whether the standard Conditions Precedent apply.
--     * Slot: customProvision Description: The custom provisions that might be specified by the parties to the agreement for the purpose of overwriting the default Condition Precedent provision specified in the CSA.
--     * Slot: specifiedConditionOrAccessCondition_id Description: Specifies the events elected by the parties that are deemed an Access Condition (for Initial Margin CSA) or a Specified Condition (for Variation Margin and Legacy CSA), which, if triggered, may temporarily or permanently suspend rights to rehypothecate, transfer, or substitute collateral.
-- # Class: ControlAgreement Description: A class to specify the relationship between the Control Agreement and the Credit Support Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: ControlAgreementElections Description: A class to specify the Control Agreement election sby each party to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: controlAgreementAsCsd Description: The identification of whether the Control Agreement is a Credit Support Document with respect to each party.
--     * Slot: consistencyWithControlAgreement Description: Unless specified as inapplicable in the event of any inconsistency between this Deed and the Control Agreement, this Deed will prevail over the Control Agreement.
--     * Slot: relationshipWithControlAgreement Description: Unless specified as inapplicable the parties recognise that the Control Agreement is a means by which the parties can perform their obligations.
--     * Slot: ControlAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: ControlAgreementNecEvent Description: A class to specify Control Agreement language related to delivery of a Notice of Exclusive Control.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: ControlAgreementNecEventElection Description: A class to specify party specific Control Agreement language related to delivery of a Notice of Exclusive Control.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: necEvent Description: Indicates Control Agreement language related to delivery of a Notice of Exclusive Control.
--     * Slot: ControlAgreementNecEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: Custodian Description: A class to specify the custodian and custody account details for each party to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CustodianElection Description: A class to specify the custodian and custody account details for each party to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: legacyVMCustodian Description: Details how the Custodian is determined.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: Custodian_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: custodian_id Description: The custody agent. While CreateiQ only specifies the custodian's name, specifying the legal entity as part of the CDM is deemed more appropriate, while this will still provide the ability to accommodate situations where only the entity name is available, as the entityId attribute is optional as part of the LegalEntity class.
--     * Slot: segregatedCashAccount_id Description: The identification of the segregated cash account for the purpose of holding cash collateral.
--     * Slot: segregatedSecurityAccount_id Description: The identification of the segregated security account for the purpose of holding security collateral.
--     * Slot: legacyNamedEntity_id Description: The identity of the relevant custodian where Named Entity is elected.
-- # Class: CustodianEvent Description: A class to specify the Custodian Event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The qualification as to whether the Custodian Event (English Law & New York Law ISDA CSA) or the Collateral Manager Event (Japanese Law ISDA CSA) is applicable.
--     * Slot: endDate_id Description: The qualification of the Custodian Event (English Law & New York Law ISDA CSA) or Collateral Manager Event (Japanese Law ISDA CSA) End Date.
-- # Class: CustodianEventEndDate Description: A class to specify the Custodian Event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: daysAfterCustodianEvent_id Description: Election to specify the number of days after the occurrence of the Custodian Event/Collateral Management Event for the purpose of qualifying the CE/CME End Date.
--     * Slot: releaseDate_id Description: Election to specify the number of days prior to the termination of the Control Agreement /Collateral Management Event for the purpose of qualifying the CE/CME End Date, in the case where advance notice is given.
--     * Slot: safekeepingPeriodExpiry_id Description: The parties' election to specify the number of days prior to the end of the safekeeping period (Clearstream CTA) purpose of qualifying the CE/CME End Date, in the case where advance notice is given.
--     * Slot: dateOfTimelyStatement_id Description: The parties' election to specify the number of days one party has effectively provided the Timely Statement to the other party.
-- # Class: CustodianRisk Description: A class to specify the Custodian Risk elections specific to a Credit Support Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CustodianRiskElection Description: A class to specify the Custodian Risk.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: isSpecified Description: The qualification as to whether the risk is deemed as Specified.
--     * Slot: qualification Description: The Custodian Risk or Collateral Manager Risk qualification.
--     * Slot: CustodianRisk_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: CustodianTerms Description: A class to specify the requirements applicable to the custodian with respect to the holding of posted collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: minimumAssets_id Description: The minimal level of assets requirement with respect to the custody agent.
--     * Slot: minimumRating_id Description: The minimal rating requirement with respect to the custody agent.
--     * Slot: initialDesignation_id Description: Election to specify the initial custodian.
-- # Class: CustodyArrangements Description: Describes how posted collateral is held, maintained, and safeguarded by a custodian or third-party agent, in accordance with the terms of the governing agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isCreditSupportDocument Description: Unless specified as True, the Control Agreement is not a Credit Support Document under the agreement with respect to a party.
--     * Slot: hasControlAgreementLanguage Description: Control Agreement language is specified when True.
--     * Slot: otherProvisions Description: Other Custom Provisions of Custody Arrangements.
--     * Slot: collateralAccessBreach_id Description: The elections specific to Collateral Access Breach language.
--     * Slot: custodianRisk_id Description: The qualification of the Custodian Risk.
--     * Slot: controlAgreement_id Description: The party-specific election with respect to the control agreement.
--     * Slot: custodianEvent_id Description: Specifies if and until when a Custodian Event clause applies.
--     * Slot: custodian_id Description: The custodian and segregated account details for each party to the agreement.
--     * Slot: collateralManagementAgreement_id Description: The designated Collateral Management Agreement with respect to the elective party as the Obligee.
-- # Class: DisputeResolution Description: A class to specify the election terms under which a party disputes the Value of any Transfer of Eligible Credit Support or Posted Credit Support.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: otherTerms Description: The custom Resolution Time election that might be specified by the parties.
--     * Slot: alternativeTerms Description: The alternative dispute resolution procedure if specified.
--     * Slot: resolutionTime_id Description: The time by which the dispute needs to be resolved, failure of which would trigger a recalculation alongside a process that is specified as part of the agreement.
--     * Slot: recalculationOfValue_id Description: The elections to specify terms for recalculation of the market value of posted collateral.
--     * Slot: legacyAlternative_id Description: Alternative procedures to those in the pre-print for resolving collateral related disputes.
--     * Slot: value_id Description: Methodology for resolving disputes in respect of the determination of the value of collateral.
-- # Class: ElectiveAmountElection Description: A class to specify the party elective amounts which can be used for the purpose of specifying elections such as the ISDA CSA Threshold and Minimum Transfer Amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: electiveAmount Description: Specifies an enumerated election to express the elective amount.
--     * Slot: customElection Description: The elective amount when expressed as a custom election by the party.
--     * Slot: MinimumTransferAmountAmendment_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: amount_id Description: The elective amount when expressed as a currency amount. The associated PartyElectiveAmount_amount data rule enforces that the currency amount is actually greater than 0.
-- # Class: EnforcementEvent Description: A class to specify Enforcement Events specific to Security Agreements.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: earlyTerminationDate Description: The early termination election.
--     * Slot: failureToPay Description: The failure to pay election.
-- # Class: ExecutionLanguage Description: A class to specify execution language terms of a Security Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: standardLanguage Description: A boolean attribute to determine if standard language is applicable or not.
--     * Slot: numberOfOriginals Description: The number of original documents.
--     * Slot: otherLanguage Description: Bespoke execution language to be included when specified.
-- # Class: ExecutionLocation Description: A class to specify execution location terms of a Security Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: executionLocation Description: The execution location of the agreement.
--     * Slot: otherLanguage Description: Bespoke execution location language to be included when specified.
--     * Slot: dutyPayer Description: The payer of documentary duty.
--     * Slot: dutyPayerLanguage Description: Bespoke terms specific to the payment of documentary duty.
--     * Slot: dutyPaymentDate Description: The date that documentary duty will be paid.
--     * Slot: dutyPaymentLanguage Description: Bespoke terms specific to the date that documentary duty will be paid.
-- # Class: ExecutionTerms Description: A class to specify execution location and language of execution to determine duty to be paid.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: executionLanguage_id Description: The bespoke execution language election.
--     * Slot: executionLocation_id Description: The bespoke execution location election.
-- # Class: FrenchLawAddendum Description: A class to specify party specific elections when a Collateral Transfer Agreement is governed by French Law.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The qualification of whether the French Law Addendum is deemed applicable by the parties (True) or not (False).
-- # Class: FrenchLawAddendumElection Description: A class to specify party specific French Law Addendum language.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The qualification of whether the party elects specific language.
--     * Slot: addendumLanguage Description: The party specific language to be included in the agreement.
--     * Slot: FrenchLawAddendum_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: FxHaircutCurrency Description: A class to specify the reference currency for the purpose of specifying the FX Haircut relating to a posting obligation, as being either the Termination Currency or an FX Designated Currency.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isTerminationCurrency Description: The reference currency for the purpose of specifying the FX Haircut relating to a posting obligation is the Termination Currency when the Boolean value is set to True.
--     * Slot: fxDesignatedCurrency Description: When specified, the reference currency for the purpose of specifying the FX Haircut relating to a posting obligation. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
-- # Class: GeneralSimmElections Description: A class to specify the ISDA SIMM as the Method for all Covered Transactions with respect to all Regimes.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: simmVersion_id Description: The qualification of the ISDA SIMM version that is specified for all Covered Transactions.
--     * Slot: simmCalculationCurrency_id Description: The SIMM Calculation Currency, as specified for each of the parties to the CSA Initial Margin.
-- # Class: HoldingAndUsingPostedCollateral Description: Specifies the conditions that need to be satisfied before the Secured Party or Custodian acting on its behalf can hold and use posted collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: HoldingAndUsingPostedCollateralElection Description: Specifies the parties' elections related to the holding and using of posted collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party to which the elections apply.
--     * Slot: useOfPostedCollateral Description: Indicates whether the party has the right to reuse, rehypothecate, or otherwise make use of the posted collateral. 'True' if the party has the right,'False' if the party does not have the right.
--     * Slot: HoldingAndUsingPostedCollateral_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: eligibilityToHoldCollateral_id Description: The specification of the conditions under which a party and its custodian(s) are entitled to hold posted collateral.
-- # Class: IneligibleCreditSupport Description: Identifies collateral that has been designated as not meeting the eligibility criteria set out in the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: totalIneligibilityDate Description: Specifies the date from which all credit support provided by a party is treated as ineligible under the agreement.
--     * Slot: transferIneligibilityDate Description: Specifies the date from which the transfer of credit support by a party is treated as ineligible under the agreement.
-- # Class: InterestAdjustment Description: A class to specify whether the Interest Adjustment is applicable and what its periodicity is.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The Interest Adjustment is applicable when True and not applicable when False.
--     * Slot: periodicity_id Description: The qualification of the Interest Adjustment periodicity.
-- # Class: InterestAdjustmentPeriodicity Description: A class to specify the Interest Adjustment periodicity.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: standardElection Description: The Interest Adjustment periodicity when specified through a standardized election.
--     * Slot: customElection Description: The Interest Adjustment periodicity when specified through a custom election.
-- # Class: InterestAmount Description: A class to specify the application of Interest Amount with respect to the Delivery Amount and the Return Amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: returnAmount_id Description: The application of Interest Amount with respect the Return Amount.
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount_id Description: The application of Interest Amount with respect the Delivery Amount.
-- # Class: JapaneseSecuritiesProvisions Description: A class to specify Japanese Securities Provision elections.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: Japanese Securities Provisions are applicable when True and Not Applicable when False.
--     * Slot: relevantProvisionsElection Description: Recommended Japanese Securities Provisions are applicable when True, additional Provisions are specified when False.
--     * Slot: relevantProvisionsTerms Description: Specific terms applicable to Recommended Japanese Securities Provisions.
--     * Slot: amendmentsToJapaneseProvisions Description: Additional Amendments to Japanese Securities Provisions are specified when True, and not specified when False.
--     * Slot: amendmentsToJapaneseProvisionsTerms Description: Specific terms applicable to Additional Amendments to Japanese Securities Provisions.
--     * Slot: clearstreamAmendmentToJapaneseProvisions Description: Specification of whether Clearstream Event amendment language is included (true) or excluded (false).
-- # Class: JurisdictionRelatedTerms Description: A class to specify terms jurisdiction related terms.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: exclusiveJurisdiction Description: Classification of optional exclusive jurisdiction terms.
--     * Slot: juryWaiver Description: The Jury Waiver conditions specific to the agreement.
--     * Slot: belgianLawSecurityAgreement Description: The qualification of whether the Belgian Law Security Agreement Addendum is deemed applicable by the parties (True) or not (False).
--     * Slot: japaneseSecuritiesProvisions_id Description: The Japanese Securities Provisions election.
--     * Slot: frenchLawAddendum_id Description: The French Law Addendum Provisions specific to the agreement.
-- # Class: MarginApproach Description: A class for selection of Margin Approach.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: marginApproach Description: Specifies the margin approach specific to Initial Margin agreements.
-- # Class: MinimumTransferAmountAmendment Description:  A class to specify whether Amendment to Minimum Transfer Amount language is applicable or not.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The definition of Minimum Transfer Amount in any Other Regulatory CSA will be amended when applicable.
--     * Slot: effectiveDate_id Description: The effective date of the Amendment to Termination Currency.
-- # Class: NotificationTime Description: Specifies the time by which a demand for the Transfer of Eligible Credit Support or Posted Credit Support needs to be made in order for the transfer to take place in accordance with the Transfer Timing provisions.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: disputeNotificationReference Description: The determination of whether reference is made to dispute resolution notification timing in the agreement.
--     * Slot: transferTimingProviso Description: The determination of whether transfer timing language is applicable or not.
-- # Class: NotificationTimeElection Description: A class to specify the notification time election by the respective parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: customNotification Description: The Notification Time as a bespoke election.
--     * Slot: localBusinessDay Description: Whether the Notification Time is precluded on the day being a local business day.
--     * Slot: NotificationTime_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: The Notification Time as a time that is qualified as a standard business center.
-- # Class: OneWayProvisions Description: A class to specify whether One Way Provisions apply.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The determination of whether the One Way Provisions are applicable (true) or not applicable (false).
--     * Slot: postingParty Description: The Posting Party for the purposes of One Way Provisions. It is specified in the case where the One Way Provision is deemed applicable.
-- # Class: OtherAgreements Description: The bespoke definition of other agreements or other credit support annex terms as specified by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: otherCSA_id Description: The bespoke definition of Other CSA as specified by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: japaneseLawCsa_id Description: The bespoke definition of whether Japanese Law CSA (VM) are specified by the parties to the agreement.
-- # Class: OtherEligibleAndPostedSupport Description: Specifies the Other Eligible Support elections.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: applicableValue Description: The definition of 'Value' with respect to Other Eligible Support and Other Posted Support.
--     * Slot: applicableTransfer Description: The definition of 'Transfer' with respect to Other Eligible Support and Other Posted Support.
--     * Slot: value_id Description: Details how particular types of collateral are valued (other than in respect of a default).
-- # Class: PartyAgreementIdentifier Description: A class defining a legal agreement identifier issued by the indicated party.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: partyReference_id Description: Party that issued the document identifier.
-- # Class: PostingObligations Description: A class to specify the collateral posting obligations of the security provider or security providers as specified in the corresponding agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: PostingObligationsElection Description: Specifies the collateral posting obligations for the security provider party(ies).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: Specifies the party providing the security.
--     * Slot: asPermitted Description: If set to True, the Control Agreement is a Credit Support Document with respect to the party(ies).
--     * Slot: excludedCollateral Description: The excluded collateral as specified in relation to the pledgor/chargor/obligor(s) posting obligation.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: PostingObligations_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: ProcessAgent Description: Specifies the Process Agent that might be appointed by the parties as part of a Credit Support Annex/Deed or Collateral Transfer Agreement.
