-- # Class: ProcessAgentElection Description: Specifies the parties' respective elections with respect to the Process Agent.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The qualification of whether the Process Agent is applicable (True) or not applicable (False).
--     * Slot: additionalInformation Description: Additional information relating to the Process Agent.
--     * Slot: partyReference Description: The party to which the election and details apply.
--     * Slot: ProcessAgent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: entity_id Description: Specification of the process agent entity.
--     * Slot: primaryContactInformation_id Description: The main notice/address information of the party.
-- # Class: RecalculationOfValue Description: A class to specify terms for Recalculation of the Market Value of Posted Collateral when a dispute has been failed to be resolved by Resolution Time.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: RecalculationOfValueElection Description: A class to specify Recalculation of Value terms that will be applicable.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: recalculationOfValueElection Description: The procedure for Recalculation of Value.
--     * Slot: recalculationOfValueTerms Description: Additional Recalculation of Value terms when specified.
--     * Slot: RecalculationOfValue_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: Regime Description: A class to specify one or more regimes that may be specified as relevant to a legal agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: fallbackToMandatoryMethodDays Description: The specification of the number of days after effective delivery of notice that Mandatory method fallback applies. Specification is only required when one or more Regimes have Fall Back to Mandatory Method elected as a SIMM exception.
-- # Class: RegimeTerms Description: A class that is used by the ApplicableRegime and the AdditionalRegime classes to specify the regulatory regime terms.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party for which the regime terms are being specified when acting as collateral taker.
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The specification of whether the regime is elected as applicable to the party when acting as collateral taker.
--     * Slot: asSpecified Description: The bespoke party specific Regime term elections applicable when specified.
--     * Slot: ApplicableRegime_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: simmException_id Description: The election for SIMM exception to the regulatory regime clause.
--     * Slot: retrospectiveEffect_id Description: Specifies the retrospective effect exception to the regulatory regime clause of Initial Margin documents as either a normalized value specified as part of an enumeration or a customized value specified of type string.
-- # Class: PledgeeRepresentativeRider Description: The terms of the Rider for the ISDA Euroclear 2019 Collateral Transfer Agreement with respect to the use of a Pledgee Representative attached to this Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: Identification of whether the representative CTA provisions are applicable (True) or not applicable (False).
--     * Slot: party Description: Identification of the represented party.
--     * Slot: representativeTerms Description: The specific representative terms applicable when specified.
--     * Slot: representativeEvent Description: The specification of whether the representative event terms are applicable.
--     * Slot: representativeEventTerms Description: The specific representative event terms applicable when specified.
--     * Slot: representativeEndDate_id Description: The definition of representative end date in relation to a representative event.
-- # Class: RetrospectiveEffect Description: A class to specify the retrospective effect exception to the regulatory regime clause of Initial Margin documents as either a normalized value specified as part of an enumeration or a customized value specified of type string.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: standardisedException Description: The Standard Initial Margin Model exception when specified by the party according to one of the enumerated values.
--     * Slot: asSpecified Description: The Standard Initial Margin Model exception when specified as a customized approach by the party.
-- # Class: RightsEvents Description: A class to specify the rights of Security Taker and/or Security Provider when an Early Termination or Access Condition event has occurred.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: deliveryInLieuRight Description: The specification of whether Delivery In Lieu language is applicable to the agreement (true) or not (false).
--     * Slot: securityTakerRightsEvent_id Description: The bespoke provisions that might be specified by the parties to the agreement applicable to a Security Taker Rights Event.
--     * Slot: controlAgreementNecEvent_id Description: The bespoke provisions that might be specified by the parties to the agreement applicable to a Notice of Exclusive Control Event.
--     * Slot: securityProviderRightsEvent_id Description: The bespoke provisions that might be specified by the parties to the agreement applicable to a Security Provider Rights Event.
--     * Slot: additionalRightsEvent_id Description: The Additional Rights Event election.
-- # Class: SecuredPartyRightsEvent Description: A class to specify Secured Party Rights Event language.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: earlyTerminationDateOptionalLanguage Description: A boolean attribute to specify whether Failure to Pay Early Termination language is included (True) or excluded (False) from the agreement.
--     * Slot: failureToPayEarlyTermination Description: A boolean attribute to specify whether Failure to Pay Early Termination language in the agreement is deemed applicable or not.
-- # Class: SecuredPartyRightsEventElection Description: A class to specify party specific Secured Party Rights Event language.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: rightsEvent Description: A boolean attribute to specify whether a Secured Party Rights Event will only occur upon the occurrence of one or more of the event specified in a Control Agreement.
--     * Slot: SecuredPartyRightsEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: SecurityProviderRightsEvent Description: A class to specify the Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor Rights Event election.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: includeCoolingOffLanguage Description: The Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor Rights Event election includes cooling off language when the attribute is set of True.
--     * Slot: fullDischarge Description: If specified as applicable here, a Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor Rights Event will not occur unless the Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor (A) has provided a statement to the Secured Party in respect of such Early Termination Date.
--     * Slot: automaticSetOff Description: The Automatic Set-Off provision applies when the value is set to True.
--     * Slot: customElection Description: A custom Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor Rights Event election might be specified by the parties.
-- # Class: SecurityProviderRightsEventElection Description: A class to specify party specific Secured Party Rights Event language.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: rightsEvent Description: If True, the Rights Event language applies for the specified Party.
--     * Slot: SecurityProviderRightsEvent_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: SensitivityMethodologies Description: A class to specificy methodologies to compute sensitivities specific to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: SensitivityMethodologiesPartyElection Description: A class to specificy methodologies to compute sensitivities specific to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party to which the election applies.
--     * Slot: SensitivityMethodologies_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: sensitivityToEquity_id Description: The methodology to compute sensitivities to equity indices, funds and ETFs for the purpose of Initial Margin agreements.
--     * Slot: sensitivityToCommodity_id Description: The methodology to compute sensitivities to commodity indices for the purpose of Initial Margin agreements.
-- # Class: SensitivityToEquity Description: Represents risk sensitivity calculated with respect to the value of an individual equity instrument.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: sensitivityToIndices_id Description: Represents risk sensitivity calculated with respect to the level of an equity or market index.
--     * Slot: sensitivityToFunds_id Description: Represents risk sensitivity calculated with respect to the value of a fund, such as a mutual fund or collective investment vehicle.
--     * Slot: sensitivityToETFs_id Description: Represents risk sensitivity calculated with respect to the value of an exchange-traded fund (ETF).
-- # Class: SensitivityMethodology Description: A class to specify the methodology according to which sensitivities are computed.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: specifiedMethodology Description: The methodology according to which sensitivities will be computed, when specified through a normalized election.
--     * Slot: customMethodology Description: The methodology according to which sensitivities will be computed, when specified through a custom election.
-- # Class: SimmCalculationCurrency Description: A class to specify the SIMM Calculation Currency elections by each party to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: SimmException Description: A class to specify the SIMM exception to the regulatory regime clause.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: standardisedException Description: The Standard Initial Margin Model exception when specified by the party according to one of the enumerated values.
--     * Slot: simmExceptionApplicable Description: The Standard Initial Margin model exception approach applicable when specified by the party according to one of the enumerated values.
--     * Slot: asSpecified Description: The Standard Initial Margin Model exception when specified as a customized approach by the party.
-- # Class: SimmVersion Description: A class to specify the ISDA SIMM version that applies to the ISDA 2018 CSA for Initial Margin.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isSpecified Description: A boolean attribute to determine whether the SIMM version is specified for the purpose of the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: partyVersion Description: The party which the specified SIMM version applies to.
--     * Slot: asSpecified Description: The SIMM version exception when specified as a customized approach by the party.
-- # Class: SubstitutedRegime Description: A class to specify each party's election with respect to the Substituted Regimes that will be applicable...
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: regime Description: The applicable regulatory regime, as specified through an enumeration.
--     * Slot: additionalRegime Description: The additional regulatory regime as specified by the parties.
--     * Slot: CreditSupportAgreementInitialMarginElections_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: CollateralTransferAgreementElections_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: SubstitutedRegimeTerms Description: Specifies the applicability of the Substituted Regime as denoted in the Substituted Regime Table as part of certain legal agreements, such as such as the ISDA 2016 and 2018 CSA for Initial Margin.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party for which the regime terms are being specified when acting as collateral taker.
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The specification of whether the regime is elected as applicable to the party when acting as collateral taker.
--     * Slot: SubstitutedRegime_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: Substitution Description: A class to specify the conditions under which the Security Provider can substitute posted collateral. The details required for 'Legacy' agreements are substantially different to those required for newer agreements; where the agreement is a 1994 or 1995 CSA, or 1995 CSD, the legacyConsent attribute needs to be used which contains additional values beyond a simple true/false value.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: SubstitutionPartyElection Description: Party specific elections for substitution of posted collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party that is acting as the Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor/Security Provider.
--     * Slot: needsConsent Description: The election as to whether the Pledgor/Obligor/Chargor/Security Provider must obtain the Secured Partys consent for any collateral substitution.
--     * Slot: substitutionDateLanguage Description: Substitution Date has the meaning specified in Paragraph4(d)(ii), unless otherwise specified.
--     * Slot: specificConsentLanguage Description: Specific consent language might be specified by the parties.
--     * Slot: legacyConsent Description: The process for substituting/exchanging one form of collateral held by a party for a different form of collateral, used with legacy agreements.
--     * Slot: Substitution_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: TerminationCurrencyAmendment Description: A class to specify the Amendment to Termination Currency elections by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: The qualification of whether the Amendment to Termination Currency is deemed applicable by the parties (True) or not (False).
--     * Slot: effectiveDate_id Description: The effective date of the Amendment to Termination Currency. This date can be specified as either an actual date, a specific date (e.g. the annex date) or as a custom provision.
-- # Class: TerminationCurrencyElection Description: A class to specify the Amendment to Termination Currency election by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isSpecified Description: The qualification of whether the Termination Currency is specified in this document (True) or in an Eligible Support Credit Support (IM) Schedule (False).
--     * Slot: currency Description: The Termination Currency associated with the party that referenced as part of this class. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.
--     * Slot: TerminationCurrencyAmendment_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: AdditionalObligations Description: The election of party specific additional obligations applicable to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party that the additional obligations apply to.
--     * Slot: additionalObligations Description: The party specific additional obligations applicable to the agreement.
-- # Class: BaseAndEligibleCurrency Description: The base and eligible currency(ies) for the document as specified by the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: baseCurrency Description: The common agreed currency into which relevant amounts of all collateral arrangements between the parties are converted, or if not an actual currency, the process through which this is determined. Where hardcoded (e.g. under the 1994 ISDA Credit Support Annex (Security Interest  NY Law)), the currency that effectively performs this function.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyTerminationCurrency Description: A flag detailing whether the Base Currency is set to  the Termination Currency as defined in the related  Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyOther Description: Utilised where the clause data structure is not able to capture a material aspect of the clause.
--     * Slot: eligibleCurrencyInclBaseCurrency Description: A flag detailing whether the Base Currency is included as an Eligible Currency.
--     * Slot: eligibleCurrencyOther Description: Utilised where the clause data structure is not able to capture a material aspect of the clause.
-- # Class: CoveredTransactions Description: Specification of Transactions covered by the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: inclusionDate Description: Includes any Transaction specified below that is entered into on or after the specified date.
--     * Slot: exposure_id Description: Specification of amendments to the calculation of Exposure in terms of the Transactions covered.
-- # Class: CreditSupportObligationsBase Description: A logical container designed to hold a set of related data. In this case, designed to hold a set of clauses that are common amongst Legacy (1994/95), Variation Margin and Initial Margin Credit Support Documents in regards to Credit Support Obligations.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be transferred to it as a Delivery Amount.
--     * Slot: returnAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be recalled to it as a Return Amount.
--     * Slot: minimumTransferAmount_id Description: Represents the threshold specified in the agreement below which collateral need not be delivered, and represents the smallest incremental value of exposure that must be reached before the parties are obliged to transfer collateral.
--     * Slot: collateralTransferTiming_id Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: bespokeTransferTiming_id Description: The time by which the transfer of collateral must take place when different from the Regular Settlement Day as a result of parties' election.
-- # Class: CreditSupportObligationsLegacy Description: Specification of the Credit Support Obligations applicable to the Legacy (1994/95) Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: threshold_id Description: Represents the amount of unsecured risk that a party is willing to tolerate without holding any posted collateral provided by the other party.
--     * Slot: rounding_id Description: The rounding methodology applicable to the Delivery Amount and the Return Amount in terms of nearest integral multiple of Base Currency units.
--     * Slot: independentAmount_id Description: Specifies the additional amount of collateral that is required to be delivered by a party irrespective of the mark-to-market exposure under the related Transactions. It may take the form of a fixed amount or may be determined using ratings.
--     * Slot: creditSupportAmount_id Description: The total amount one counterparty must deliver to the other at any time: the combination of the Exposure to that party and the net Independent Amounts it must post, minus any agreed Threshold.
--     * Slot: eligibleCreditSupport_id Description: Specification of the Eligible Collateral or Credit Support applicable to the Agreement.
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be transferred to it as a Delivery Amount.
--     * Slot: returnAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be recalled to it as a Return Amount.
--     * Slot: minimumTransferAmount_id Description: Represents the threshold specified in the agreement below which collateral need not be delivered, and represents the smallest incremental value of exposure that must be reached before the parties are obliged to transfer collateral.
--     * Slot: collateralTransferTiming_id Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: bespokeTransferTiming_id Description: The time by which the transfer of collateral must take place when different from the Regular Settlement Day as a result of parties' election.
-- # Class: CreditSupportObligationsInitialMargin Description: Specification of the Credit Support Obligations applicable to the Initial Margin Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: otherEligibleSupportIM Description: The Other Eligible Support election. If not specified, this election is deemed as not applicable.
--     * Slot: marginApproach_id Description: The selection of Margin Approach applicable to the agreement.
--     * Slot: rounding_id Description: The rounding methodology applicable to the Delivery Amount and the Return Amount in terms of nearest integral multiple of Base Currency units.
--     * Slot: threshold_id Description: Represents the amount of unsecured risk that a party is willing to tolerate without holding any posted collateral provided by the other party.
--     * Slot: creditSupportAmount_id Description: The total amount one counterparty must deliver to the other at any time: the combination of the Exposure to that party and the net Independent Amounts it must post, minus any agreed Threshold.
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be transferred to it as a Delivery Amount.
--     * Slot: returnAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be recalled to it as a Return Amount.
--     * Slot: minimumTransferAmount_id Description: Represents the threshold specified in the agreement below which collateral need not be delivered, and represents the smallest incremental value of exposure that must be reached before the parties are obliged to transfer collateral.
--     * Slot: collateralTransferTiming_id Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: bespokeTransferTiming_id Description: The time by which the transfer of collateral must take place when different from the Regular Settlement Day as a result of parties' election.
-- # Class: CreditSupportObligationsCollateralTransferAgreement Description: Specification of the Credit Support Obligations applicable to the Initial Margin Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: otherEligibleSupportIM Description: The Other Eligible Support election. If not specified, this election is deemed as not applicable.
--     * Slot: marginApproach_id Description: The selection of Margin Approach applicable to the agreement.
--     * Slot: threshold_id Description: Represents the amount of unsecured risk that a party is willing to tolerate without holding any posted collateral provided by the other party.
--     * Slot: creditSupportAmount_id Description: The total amount one counterparty must deliver to the other at any time: the combination of the Exposure to that party and the net Independent Amounts it must post, minus any agreed Threshold.
--     * Slot: rounding_id Description: The rounding methodology applicable to the Delivery Amount and the Return Amount in terms of nearest integral multiple of Base Currency units.
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be transferred to it as a Delivery Amount.
--     * Slot: returnAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be recalled to it as a Return Amount.
--     * Slot: minimumTransferAmount_id Description: Represents the threshold specified in the agreement below which collateral need not be delivered, and represents the smallest incremental value of exposure that must be reached before the parties are obliged to transfer collateral.
--     * Slot: collateralTransferTiming_id Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: bespokeTransferTiming_id Description: The time by which the transfer of collateral must take place when different from the Regular Settlement Day as a result of parties' election.
-- # Class: CreditSupportObligationsVariationMargin Description: Specification of the Credit Support Obligations applicable to the Variation Margin Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: fxHaircut Description: The alternative definition for FX haircut percentage that applies to each party and item of Eligible Collateral unless this item is denominated in a Major Currency or in the Base Currency.
--     * Slot: ineligibleCreditSupport_id Description: The parties to which the provisions of the Credit Support Annex for Variation Margin will apply to.
--     * Slot: rounding_id Description: The rounding methodology applicable to the Delivery Amount and the Return Amount in terms of nearest integral multiple of Base Currency units.
--     * Slot: eligibleCreditSupport_id Description: Specification of the Eligible Collateral or Credit Support applicable to the Agreement.
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be transferred to it as a Delivery Amount.
--     * Slot: returnAmount_id Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be recalled to it as a Return Amount.
--     * Slot: minimumTransferAmount_id Description: Represents the threshold specified in the agreement below which collateral need not be delivered, and represents the smallest incremental value of exposure that must be reached before the parties are obliged to transfer collateral.
--     * Slot: collateralTransferTiming_id Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: bespokeTransferTiming_id Description: The time by which the transfer of collateral must take place when different from the Regular Settlement Day as a result of parties' election.
-- # Class: EligibleCreditSupport Description: Specifies the collateral posting obligations of the security provider or security providers as specified in the corresponding agreement
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: EligibleCollateralElection Description: Specifies the collateral posting obligations for the security provider party(ies).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: otherEligibleSupport Description: Specifies the Other Eligible Support conditions. If not specified, this election is deemed as not applicable.
--     * Slot: party Description: Specifies the party providing the security.
--     * Slot: asPermitted Description: If set to True, the Control Agreement is a Credit Support Document with respect to the party(ies).
--     * Slot: excludedCollateral Description: The excluded collateral as specified in relation to the pledgor/chargor/obligor(s) posting obligation.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: EligibleCreditSupport_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: SecurityInterestForObligations Description: Security Interest for Obligations clause applicable to 1994 NY CSA, 1995 English Law CSA, 1995 English Law Credit Support Deed, 2016 English Law VM CSA and 2016 New York Law VM CSA.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: obligations Description: A description of any additional obligations secured by the credit support arrangements.
--     * Slot: obligee Description: The party to whom obligations under the Master Agreement are owed and secured by the credit support arrangements.
--     * Slot: other Description: Exception value.
-- # Class: SinglePostingParty Description: Where only a single  party is explicitly designated to post collateral, the party which is specified as the sole poster of collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party acting as the Single Posting Party.
--     * Slot: other Description: Utilised where the clause data structure is not able to capture a material aspect of the clause.
-- # Class: Threshold Description: Represents the amount of unsecured risk that a party is willing to tolerate without holding any posted collateral provided by the other party.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: ThresholdMinimumTransferAmountBase Description: A logical container designed to hold a set of related data. In this case, designed to hold a set of information required to specify conditions under which Threshold or Minimum Transfer Amount can fall to zero.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: zeroEvent Description: Indicates whether a trigger applies for the Threshold or Minimum Transfer Amount to fall to zero. If 'True' then such a trigger exists.
-- # Class: ThresholdElection Description: Specifies whether the threshold is rating based, a fixed amount, or infinity.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party to which the threshold applies.
--     * Slot: infinity Description: Specifies that the Threshold is Infinity. If 'True' then the threshold for the elective party is Infinity.
--     * Slot: other Description: Utilised where the clause data structure is not able to capture a material aspect of the clause.
--     * Slot: Threshold_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: fixedAmount_id Description: Defines that the Threshold is a Fixed Amount.
--     * Slot: ratingsBased_id Description: Defines that the Threshold is based on a Ratings condition(s).
-- # Class: ThresholdRatingsBased Description: Defines that the Threshold is based on Ratings condition(s).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: currency Description: The threshold currency code.
--     * Slot: ratingType Description: The relevant rating type.
--     * Slot: ratedParty Description: The party to which a rating applies.
--     * Slot: namedEntity Description: Details the Named Entity where the Rated Party is Named Entity.
--     * Slot: namedAffiliate Description: Details the Named Affiliate where the Rated Party is Named Affiliate.
--     * Slot: compare Description: Where two ratings are specified whether the higher or lower rating prevails.
--     * Slot: noRating Description: What conditions apply where a party has no rating.
--     * Slot: notRatedBy Description: Defines where conditions apply if no Rating where ratings may not exist.
--     * Slot: numberOfRatingAgencies Description: Defines the number of Rating Agencies that the Party must be rated by.
--     * Slot: zeroEvent Description: Indicates whether a trigger applies for the Threshold or Minimum Transfer Amount to fall to zero. If 'True' then such a trigger exists.
-- # Class: CSAThresholdVariableSet Description: Defines a combination of Rating Agency, Rating Value, Threshold amount and Currency code.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The relevant rating agency.
--     * Slot: value Description: Rating applicable to the party from a given rating agency.
--     * Slot: amount Description: The amount value applicable to the Threshold.
--     * Slot: ThresholdRatingsBased_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MinimumTransferAmount Description: Represents the threshold specified in the agreement below which collateral need not be delivered, and represents the smallest incremental value of exposure that must be reached before the parties are obliged to transfer collateral.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: MinimumTransferAmountElection Description: Specifies the method by which the minimum transfer amount is defined, such as a fixed amount, ratings based, or an alternative basis set out in the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The party to which the minimum transfer amount applies.
--     * Slot: other Description: Utilised where the clause data structure is not able to capture a material aspect of the clause.
--     * Slot: MinimumTransferAmount_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: fixedAmount_id Description: Defines that the Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) is a Fixed Amount.
--     * Slot: ratingsBased_id Description: Defines that the Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) is based on a Ratings condition(s).
-- # Class: ThresholdMinimumTransferAmountFixedAmount Description: Defines the Threshold or the Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) as a fixed amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: zeroEvent Description: Indicates whether a trigger applies for the Threshold or Minimum Transfer Amount to fall to zero. If 'True' then such a trigger exists.
--     * Slot: amount_id Description: Specifies the monetary value of the Threshold or the Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) applicable to collateral transfer obligations.
-- # Class: MinimumTransferAmountRatingsBased Description: Defines that the Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) is based on a Ratings condition(s).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: currency Description: The minimum transfer amount currency code.
--     * Slot: ratingType Description: The relevant rating type.
--     * Slot: ratedParty Description: The party to which a rating applies.
--     * Slot: namedEntity Description: Details the Named Entity where the Rated Party is Named Entity.
--     * Slot: namedAffiliate Description: Details the Named Affiliate where the Rated Party is Named Affiliate.
--     * Slot: compare Description: Where two ratings are specified whether the higher or lower rating prevails.
--     * Slot: noRating Description: What conditions apply where a party has no rating.
--     * Slot: notRatedBy Description: Defines where conditions apply if no Rating where ratings may not exist.
--     * Slot: numberOfRatingAgencies Description: Defines the number of Rating Agencies that the Party must be rated by.
--     * Slot: zeroEvent Description: Indicates whether a trigger applies for the Threshold or Minimum Transfer Amount to fall to zero. If 'True' then such a trigger exists.
-- # Class: CSAMinimumTransferAmountVariableSet Description: Defines a combination of Rating Agency, Rating Value, amount and Currency code.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the Rating Agency.
--     * Slot: value Description: The value assigned to the rating.
--     * Slot: amount Description: The Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) applicable to the Rating.
--     * Slot: amountIsInfinity Description: A flag that defines the Minimum Transfer Amount (MTA) as Infinity.
--     * Slot: MinimumTransferAmountRatingsBased_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MasterAgreementDatedAsOfDate Description: Defines the dates agreed by the parties as the date of the Credit Support Annex or Credit Support Deed.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: masterAgreementDatedAsOfDate Description: The date agreed by the parties as the Dated as of Date for the Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CSADeliveryAmount Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be transferred to it as a Delivery Amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: deliveryAmount Description: Specifies whether the meaning of Delivery Amount follows the pre-print definition or deviates from this (either based on a rating or some other methodology).
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CSAReturnAmount Description: In respect of a Valuation Date, the amount of collateral which a party is entitled to demand to be recalled to it as a Return Amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: returnAmount Description: Specifies whether the meaning of Return Amount follows the pre-print definition or deviates from this (either based on a rating or some other methodology).
-- # Class: ValuationTime Description: Specifies the time by which the value of the collateral and obligations to transfer or return collateral are to be calculated relative to the Valuation Date.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: day Description: The day in respect of which the Valuation Time is being specified. If not specified, addional language must be used to define the methodology.
--     * Slot: time Description: The type of time specified for the Valuation Time.
--     * Slot: hourminutetime Description: A time specified in a 24-hour notation, e.g. 3pm would be represented as 15:00.
--     * Slot: timezone Description: Any relevant time zone where specified.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: FinalReturns Description: A clause providing that final return collateral is to be provided without consideration of any Minimum Transfer Amount and collateral haircut.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: applicable Description: Defines if the clause is applicable to this agreement or any other exceptions.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CSAValuationDate Description: Specifies the date on which the value of collateral or exposure are calculated in accordance with the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: date Description: Defines whether a date is defined by a certain day of the week or a particular date in the month. If not specified here, then additional language must be used.
--     * Slot: day Description: Specific day(s) or day of the week, if any, specified for Valuation Time.
--     * Slot: calendarDay Description: Defines the day of the calendar if this is specified for in the ValuationDateDateEnum.
--     * Slot: frequency Description: Defines the regularity of the date specified for the Valuation Date.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: ValuationAgent Description: Details of the party valuating the collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: Specification of which party calculating the value of collateral to be delivered or returned.
--     * Slot: valuationAgent Description: Specifies how the Valuation Agent is determined.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: ExposureScope Description: Optionally, for each party, specifies the amendments to the included coverage in the calculation of Exposure.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: LegacyExposureScopeElection Description: Specification of amendments to the calculation of Exposure in terms of the Transactions and Products covered.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The elective party.
--     * Slot: excludedTransactions Description: A boolean flag to represent whether any transactions are excluded (ie True) or not (ie False).
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The bespoke/additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: ExposureScope_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: ExcludedProducts Description: Description of the relevant derivative transactions excluded from the calculation of exposure.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: excluded Description: A flag to indicate whether transactions entered into by a specific branch with respect to the relevant party are excluded; set to True if excluded, false if included.
--     * Slot: LegacyExposureScopeElection_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: CreditSupportAmount Description: The total amount one counterparty must deliver to the other at any time: the combination of the Exposure to that party and the net Independent Amounts it must post, minus any agreed Threshold.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: creditSupportAmount Description: Specifies whether the meaning of credit support amount follows the pre-print definition or deviates from the standard (either based on a rating or some other methodology).
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: LegacyResolutionAlternative Description: Alternative procedures to those in the pre-print for resolving collateral related disputes.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: resolutionAlternative Description: Details of the alternative dispute resolution procedure (if any).
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
--     * Slot: amount_id Description: The maximum amount to which the difference between the calculations by the valuation agent and disputing party can be split, where Split the Difference is elected.
-- # Class: ResolutionValue Description: Methodology for resolving disputes in respect of the determination of the value of collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cash Description: Details of how cash collateral is valued when resolving disputes.
--     * Slot: securities Description: Details of how securities collateral is valued when resolving disputes.
--     * Slot: fallback Description: Represents whether a fallback calculation method is applicable. 'True' if fallback calculation method is applicable.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CollateralTransferTiming Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: transferSettlementTiming_id Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: collateralTransferTimingDefinition_id Description: Bespoke language removing the pre-print requirement to transfer legal title of securities collateral through written instructions to the relevant depository institution or other securities intermediaries solely for the purposes of the 1994 New York Law Credit Support Annex.
-- # Class: TransferSettlementTiming Description: Specification of transfer / settlement timing for cash and securities collateral assuming that the notice is provided before the Notification Time (and with a 1LBD lag introduced if the notice is delivered after the Notification Time), and that securities allow for a further Local Business Day for transfer / settlement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cashCollateralTransferSettlementTime Description: Details the day on which collateral is required to be transferred relative to the Notification Time.
--     * Slot: securititesCollateralTransferSettlementTime Description: Details the day on which collateral is required to be transferred relative to the Notification Time.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CollateralTransferTimingDefinition Description: Bespoke language removing the pre-print requirement to transfer legal title of securities collateral through written instructions to the relevant depository institution or other securities intermediaries solely for the purposes of the 1994 New York Law Credit Support Annex.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: A boolean flag to represent bespoke amendment to the pre-print definition of Transfer.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CollateralValueMethod Description: Details how particular types of collateral are valued (other than in respect of a default).
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cashCollateral Description: Details of how cash collateral is valued.
--     * Slot: securitiesCollateral Description: Details of how securities collateral is valued.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: CreditSupportDocument Description: Identification of party specific Credit Support Documents applicable to the document.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CreditSupportDocumentElection Description: The party election of Credit Support Provider(s), if any.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: creditSupportDocumentTerms Description: Specification of the Credit Support Document terms.
--     * Slot: bespokeCreditSuppportDocument Description: Specification of a document when not captured under RelatedAgreement.
--     * Slot: CreditSupportDocument_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: party_id Description: The elective party.
-- # Class: CreditSupportProvider Description: Identification of party specific Credit Support Providers applicable to the document.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: CreditSupportProviderElection Description: The party election of Credit Support Provider(s), if any.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: creditSupportProviderTerms Description: Specification of the Credit Support Provider terms.
--     * Slot: bespokeCreditSuppportProvider Description: ...
--     * Slot: CreditSupportProvider_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: party_id Description: The elective party.
-- # Class: SpecifiedConditionOrAccessCondition Description: Specifies the events elected by the parties that are deemed an Access Condition (for Initial Margin CSA) or a Specified Condition (for Variation Margin and Legacy CSA), which, if triggered, may temporarily or permanently suspend rights to rehypothecate, transfer, or substitute collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: Indicates whether events that could temporarily or permanently suspend rights to rehypothecate, transfer or substitute collateral are applicable. If applicable,'True'. If not applicable,'False'.
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: SpecifiedOrAccessConditionPartyElection Description: The party specific elections in respect to the Specified Condition and Access Condition clause.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: Identifies the party making the election.
--     * Slot: SpecifiedConditionOrAccessCondition_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: LegacyIndependentAmount Description: Sets out the additional amount of collateral that is required to be delivered by that party irrespective of the mark-to-market exposure under the related Transactions. It may take the form of a fixed amount, or be determined using credit ratings.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: additionalLanguage Description: The additional language that might be specified by the parties to the legal agreement.
-- # Class: LegacyIndependentAmountParty Description: The party specific elections for the Independent Amount clause.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: Identifies the Party making the election.
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: Specifies whether Independent Amount is applicable to the elected party. If applicable, 'True', and if not applicable then 'False'.
--     * Slot: LegacyIndependentAmount_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: fixedAmount_id Description: Indicates the Independent Amount is specified as a fixed amount.
--     * Slot: ratingsBased_id Description: Indicates the Independent Amount is determined using a credit rating.
--     * Slot: ratingsXExposure_id Description: Indicates the Independent Amount is determined using both credit rating and exposure metrics.
-- # Class: IndependentAmountRatings Description: A logical container designed to hold a set of related data. In this case, designed to hold a set of information required when Independent Amount is determined using credit ratings.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: compare Description: Specifies how multiple credit ratings are compared when determining the applicable Independent Amount, and whether that measure is highest, lowest, or a comparison of either.
--     * Slot: ratedParty Description: Specifies the party to whom the rating agency rating applies to for the purposes of determining the Independent Amount.
--     * Slot: ratingType Description: The relevant rating type.
--     * Slot: namedAffiliate_id Description: Details the Named Affiliate where the Rated Party is Named Affiliate.
--     * Slot: namedEntity_id Description: Details the Named Entity where the Rated Party is Named Entity.
-- # Class: LegacyIndependentAmountRatingsBased Description: Specifies that the Independent Amount is determined using a credit rating.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: currency Description: Specifies the currency applicable to the relevant Independent Amount.
--     * Slot: compare Description: Specifies how multiple credit ratings are compared when determining the applicable Independent Amount, and whether that measure is highest, lowest, or a comparison of either.
--     * Slot: ratedParty Description: Specifies the party to whom the rating agency rating applies to for the purposes of determining the Independent Amount.
--     * Slot: ratingType Description: The relevant rating type.
--     * Slot: namedAffiliate_id Description: Details the Named Affiliate where the Rated Party is Named Affiliate.
--     * Slot: namedEntity_id Description: Details the Named Entity where the Rated Party is Named Entity.
-- # Class: RatingAgencyAmount Description: A logical container to hold a defined set of related data. In this case the collation of Rating Information and an associated Independent Amount.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: amount Description: Specifies the notional or collateral Independent Amount.
--     * Slot: LegacyIndependentAmountRatingsBased_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: LegacyIndependentAmountRatingsXExposure Description: Specifies that the Independent Amount is determined using both credit rating and exposure metrics.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: compare Description: Specifies how multiple credit ratings are compared when determining the applicable Independent Amount, and whether that measure is highest, lowest, or a comparison of either.
--     * Slot: ratedParty Description: Specifies the party to whom the rating agency rating applies to for the purposes of determining the Independent Amount.
--     * Slot: ratingType Description: The relevant rating type.
--     * Slot: namedAffiliate_id Description: Details the Named Affiliate where the Rated Party is Named Affiliate.
--     * Slot: namedEntity_id Description: Details the Named Entity where the Rated Party is Named Entity.
-- # Class: RatingMultiplier Description: A logical container to hold a defined set of related data. In this case the collation of Ratings Information and associated exposure multiplier.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: exposureMultiplier Description: Specifies the multiplier applied to exposure based on the credit rating of the rated party.
--     * Slot: LegacyIndependentAmountRatingsXExposure_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: DirectionRatingMultiplier Description: A logical container to hold a defined set of related data. In this case the collation of Ratings Information and associated exposure multiplier.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: exposureMultiplier Description: Specifies the multiplier applied to exposure based on the credit rating of the rated party.
--     * Slot: LegacyIndependentAmountRatingsXExposure_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: AllDirectionRating Description: Used to combine two or more Ratings and associated direction using AND logic.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: AnyDirectionRating Description: Used to combine two or more Ratings and associated direction using OR logic.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: DirectionRating Description: A logical container to hold a defined set of related data. In this case the collation of Ratings Agency, Rating value and an associated direction.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: direction Description: Specifies the direction of measurement for the rated party.
--     * Slot: agency Description: Specifies The credit agency to which the other variables (notation, scale, debt type) refer to.
--     * Slot: notation Description: Specifies The credit rating notation. As it varies among credit rating agencies, FpML doesn't specify a default scheme.
--     * Slot: scale Description: Specifies the credit rating scale, with a typical distinction between short term, long term. FpML doesn't specify a default scheme, which is hence not specified as an enumeration as part of the CDM.
--     * Slot: outlook Description: Assesses the potential direction of a long-term credit rating over the intermediate term, which is generally up to two years for investment grade and generally up to one year for speculative grade.
--     * Slot: creditWatch Description: Indicates the potential direction of a short-term or long-term rating. It focuses on identifiable events and short-term trends that cause ratings to be placed under special surveillance.
--     * Slot: debt_id Description: Specifies the credit rating debt type (e.g. long term, high yield, deposits, ...) associated with the credit rating notation and scale.
-- # Class: EligibilityToHoldCollateral Description: Specifies the conditions under which a party and its custodian(s) are entitled to hold collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: custodianEligibility Description: Specifies whether the party's custodian is eligible to hold the other party's posted collateral. If 'True' then the custodian is eligible to hold the Posted Collateral given that the specified criteria are met.
--     * Slot: custodianCondition Description: Specifies any additional conditions relevant to the Custodian of the respective parties as set out in the Holding and Using Posted Collateral clause.
--     * Slot: initialCustodian_id Description: Election to specify the initial custodian.
--     * Slot: criteria_id Description: A logical container to hold a defined set of related data. In this case the collation of criteria required by the party and its custodian to Hold the other party's Posted Collateral.
-- # Class: AllEligibilityToHoldCollateralCriteria Description: Used to combine two or more Criteria using AND logic.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: AnyEligibilityToHoldCollateralCriteria Description: Used to combine two or more Criteria using OR logic.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: AmountOfNetCapital Description: The amount of net capital.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: amountOfNetCapital_id Description: The amount of net capital.
-- # Class: RatingAgencyValue Description: A logical container designed to hold a set of related data. In this case the Rating Agency, Rating Value and Rating Type.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: ratingType Description: The relevant rating type.
--     * Slot: agency Description: Specifies The credit agency to which the other variables (notation, scale, debt type) refer to.
--     * Slot: notation Description: Specifies The credit rating notation. As it varies among credit rating agencies, FpML doesn't specify a default scheme.
--     * Slot: scale Description: Specifies the credit rating scale, with a typical distinction between short term, long term. FpML doesn't specify a default scheme, which is hence not specified as an enumeration as part of the CDM.
--     * Slot: outlook Description: Assesses the potential direction of a long-term credit rating over the intermediate term, which is generally up to two years for investment grade and generally up to one year for speculative grade.
--     * Slot: creditWatch Description: Indicates the potential direction of a short-term or long-term rating. It focuses on identifiable events and short-term trends that cause ratings to be placed under special surveillance.
--     * Slot: debt_id Description: Specifies the credit rating debt type (e.g. long term, high yield, deposits, ...) associated with the credit rating notation and scale.
-- # Class: DemandsAndNotices Description: Specifies the address where the demands, specifications and notices will be communicated to for each of the parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: deemedEffectiveNextLBD Description: Specifies if notice shall be deemed to be effective at the time such notice is actually received unless such notice is received on a day which is not a Local Business Day or after the Notification Time on any Local Business Day in which event such notice shall be deemed to be effective on the next succeeding Local Business Day. If deemed effective,'True'. If not deemed effective, or not stated,'False'.
-- # Class: AddressesForTransfer Description: Specifies the address for transfer as specified by the respective parties to the agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Abstract Class: CreditSupportAgreementElections Description: The set of elections which specify a Credit Support Annex or Deed.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Abstract Class: DirectionRatingSet Description: A logical container to hold a defined set of related data. In this case the collation of Ratings Agency, Rating value and an associated direction that are grouped by either AND or OR logic.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: DirectionRatingMultiplier_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: AllDirectionRating_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: AnyDirectionRating_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Abstract Class: EligibilityToHoldCollateralCriteria Description: Defines a set of Criteria required by the party and its custodian to hold the other party's Posted Collateral.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: AllEligibilityToHoldCollateralCriteria_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: AnyEligibilityToHoldCollateralCriteria_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MasterAgreementSchedule Description: The set of elections which specify a Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: MasterAgreementClause Description: Defines clauses that make up a Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifer Description: Unique identifier for the clause.
--     * Slot: name Description: Optional textual description of the clause.
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementSchedule_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MasterAgreementClauseVariant Description: Sets the details for a specific variant associated to a clause in a Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: identifier Description: Unique identifier for this variant.
--     * Slot: name Description: Optional textual description of the variant.
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementClause_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MasterAgreementVariableSet Description: Defines a type where additional variables associated to clauses and their variants can be described.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the variable.
--     * Slot: value Description: The value for this variable.
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementClauseVariant_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementVariableSet_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: MasterAgreementBase Description: A set of elections that can be shared across master agreement types - this should be built upon for specific contracts.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: MasterAgreementElections Description: A representation of a master agreement extended from a base agreement of shared elections.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: GlobalMasterRepoAgreement Description: The set of elections that define a GMRA
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: MasterAgreement Description: The set of elections that define an ISDA Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: nonContractualObligations Description: Specification of whether the Governing Law clause extends to Non-Contractual Obligations (True) or does not extend to Non-Contractual Obligations (False).
--     * Slot: automaticEarlyTermination_id Description: The specification of whether there is an automatic occurrence of an Early Termination Date in respect of Transactions upon the occurrence of certain bankruptcy / insolvency related events.
--     * Slot: terminationCurrency_id Description: Specification of the currency in which the termination payment is made (including the process by which such currency is determined).
--     * Slot: addressForNotices_id Description: Specification of the address and other details for notices.
--     * Slot: creditSupportDocument_id Description: Identification of party specific Credit Support Documents applicable to the document.
--     * Slot: creditSupportProvider_id Description: Identification of party specific Credit Support Providers applicable to the document.
-- # Class: AutomaticEarlyTermination Description: A class to specify the Automatic Early Termination provision applicable to a Master Agreement.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: fallbackAET Description: Specifies whether automatic termination applies in the event of certain bankruptcy events.
--     * Slot: indemnity Description: Specifies whether indemnity applies in the event AET is applicable to one or both of the parties.
-- # Class: AutomaticEarlyTerminationElection Description: A class to specify the party elections specific to the Automatic Early Termination Clause.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: isApplicable Description: A boolean election to specify whether the Automatic Early Termination provisions of Section 6(a) are applicable (True) or not applicable (False).
--     * Slot: AutomaticEarlyTermination_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: party_id Description: The party for which the Automatic Early Termination provisions are being specified.
-- # Class: TerminationCurrency Description: Specifies how the Termination Currency for the agreement will be determined.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: statedTerminationCurrency_id Description: Allows for specific Termination Currency(ies) and a fallback Termination Currency to be selected.
--     * Slot: partyOptionTerminationCurrency_id Description: Provides that the Termination Currency will be determined by reference to a contractual mechanism when closing out the Agreement.
-- # Class: TerminationCurrencySelection Description: Specifies Termination Currency where a currency is stated at the time the agreement is entered into.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: statedCurrency Description: Specifies a single Termination Currency for the agreement.
--     * Slot: fallbackCurrency Description: Specifies a single fallback Termination Currency should the stated currency not be freely available.
--     * Slot: bothAffected Description: Specifies fallback Termination Currency where both parties are Affected Parties.
-- # Class: PartyOptionTerminationCurrency Description: Specifies mechanism for Termination currency to be selected by the Non-defaulting Party/party which is not the Affected Party.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: bothAffectedTermCurrencyOption Description: Specifies termination currency where there are two Affected Parties and they cannot agree on the termination currency.
--     * Slot: terminationCurrencySpecifiedCondition Description: Specifies alternative conditions for selection of the termination currency.
--     * Slot: terminationCurrencyCondition Description: Specifies the enumerated conditions for selection of the termination currency.
-- # Class: PartyTerminationCurrencySelection Description: Specifies the termination currency to be used by a party when it is the Non-Defaulting Party or the Party which is not the Affected Party.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: statedPartyCurrency Description: Specifies termination Currency.
--     * Slot: TerminationCurrencySelection_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: party_id Description: The elective party.
-- # Class: SpecifiedEntities Description: A provision that allows each party to specify its Specified Entities for certain Events of Default and Termination Events.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: specifiedEntityClause Description: The Event of Default or Termination event for which Specified Entities terms are being defined.
--     * Slot: MasterAgreement_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: SpecifiedEntity Description: The party specific election of Specified Entities for the Event of Default or Termination Event specified.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: specifiedEntityTerms Description: The specified entity terms for the Event of Default or Termination Event specified.
--     * Slot: materialSubsidiaryTerms Description: The meaning of Material Subsidiary for the Event of Default or Termination Event specified.
--     * Slot: otherSpecifiedEntityTerms Description: The non standard terms for the Event of Default or Termination Event specified.
--     * Slot: SpecifiedEntities_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: party_id Description: The elective party.
-- # Class: GlobalMasterSecuritiesLendingAgreement Description: The set of elections that define a GMSLA.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: collateral_id Description: The definitions regarding collateral relating to the GMSLA.
--     * Slot: baseCurrency_id Description: The definitions regarding base currency determinations relating to the GMSLA.
--     * Slot: eventsOfDefault_id Description: The definitions regarding any different events of default relating to the GMSLA.
-- # Class: CollateralSpecification Description: The definitions regarding collateral relating to the GMSLA.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: standardDefinitionOfMarketValueUsed Description: Is the standard definition of 'Market Value' used in the GMSLA?
--     * Slot: definitionOfMarketValueNonStandard Description: If the definition of 'Market Value' is non standard, it can be specified here.
--     * Slot: nettingObligationsApply Description: Does paragraph 5.6 (netting of obligations to deliver Collateral and redeliver Equivalent Collateral) apply to the GMSLA?
--     * Slot: failureToDevliverIndemnityApplies Description: Does paragraph 6.4 (indemnity for failure to redeliver Equivalent Non-Cash Collateral) apply to the GMSLA?
--     * Slot: aggregation_id Description: How does paragraph 5.4 (aggregation) apply to the GMSLA?
--     * Slot: notificationTime_id Description: What is the notification time of the GMSLA?
-- # Class: BaseCurrency Description: The definitions regarding base currency determinations relating to the GMSLA.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: baseCurrency Description: The base currency as defined in the GMSLA.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyMustBeFreelyConvertible Description: The base currency that is defined must be freely convertible.
--     * Slot: baseCurrencyIfOriginalNotFreelyConvertible Description: If the base currency is not freely convertible, the fallback currency can be defined here.
-- # Class: EventsOfDefaultElection Description: The specific party elections for events of default.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: party Description: The specified party.
--     * Slot: automaticEarlyTerminationApplies Description: Does automatic early termination apply to the specified party?
--     * Slot: existingLoans Description: Are existing loans covered in the event of default (Only relevant to 2010 GMSLAs)?
--     * Slot: automation Description: Are third party vendors allowed to automate the processing of loans in the event of default (Only relevant to 2010 GMSLAs)?
--     * Slot: automaticEarlyTerminationSpecifiedSeparatelyForEachPrinciple Description: In the case where party is acting as an agent, is automatic early termination specified on a per principle basis?
--     * Slot: automaticEarlyTerminationRequiredDueToSystemOfLaw Description: Automatic early termination only applies if required due to system of law, otherwise it is not applicable.
--     * Slot: automaticEarlyTerminationInModifiedForm Description: Automatic early termination applies in a modified form only.
--     * Slot: automaticEarlyTerminationOther Description: Optional string to capture any further information regarding the automatic early termination even of default.
--     * Slot: EventsOfDefault_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
-- # Class: EventsOfDefault Description: The definitions regarding any different events of default relating to the GMSLA.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: Aggregation Description: The definitions for whether aggregation applies to the GMSLA, and if so how it applies.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: aggregationType Description: How is the mark to market value determined?
