-- # Class: MasterAgreementClause_counterparty
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementClause_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: counterparty Description: Optional counterparty role. This can be used where a clause needs to be assigned to a specific party on the agreement based upon their role i.e. Party A or Party B.
-- # Class: MasterAgreementClause_otherParty
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementClause_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: otherParty Description: Optional party. This can be required for umbrella agreements where a clause may need to be assigned to a specific party who may or may not be on the agreement.
-- # Class: MasterAgreementClauseVariant_counterparty
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementClauseVariant_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: counterparty Description: Optional counterparty role. This can be used where a clause needs to assign a different variant to the different parties on the agreement based upon their role i.e. Party A or Party B.
-- # Class: MasterAgreementClauseVariant_otherParty
--     * Slot: MasterAgreementClauseVariant_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: otherParty Description: Optional party. This can be used where a clause needs to assign different variants to different parties who may or may not be on the agreement.
-- # Class: UnderlierSubstitutionProvision_whoMaySubstitute
--     * Slot: UnderlierSubstitutionProvision_id Description: Autocreated FK slot
--     * Slot: whoMaySubstitute Description: Designates which Counterparty to the transaction who has the right to trigger a substitution or to provide related determination e.g. for instance to qualify the effectiveness of an Event which may be a trigger for substitution, determine the replacement Share to substitute, etc. ; cardinality of this object is 2, in case parties jointly have this role.
